Notre raison d'être

TOUJOURS FAIRE MIEUX.

Nos valeurs nous incitent à nous surpasser et orientent nos actions pour repousser sans cesse les limites du possible, jour après jour. Nos équipes adoptent un esprit d’amélioration continue et remettent constamment en question le statu quo. Nous prenons plaisir à ressentir la fierté et l’effet « wow » lorsque nous dépassons nos limites, introduisons une nouvelle idée, ou trouvons simplement une solution à un problème.

SOLIDARITÉ

Je supporte mon équipe, comme elle me supporte.

RÉSILIENCE

Je fais face aux défis.

EXCELLENCE

J'excelle, sans compromis.

OUVERTURE D'ESPRIT

J'ose sortir de ma zone de confort.

Innovation

Notre équipe adopte une philosophie de remise en question du statu quo. Nous sommes ouverts aux nouvelles idées et toujours en quête d’opportunités d’amélioration. Notre curiosité nous pousse à poser des questions, à explorer de nouvelles méthodes et à mettre en place des outils innovants pour favoriser l’amélioration continue.

Unmatched Expertise
Meet The NexKemia Specialty Product Line

NexKemia stands out in the market because of our multifaceted product line. We prioritize client success by not just delivering a unique variety of custom expandable polystyrene resins (EPS), but by establishing long-term partnerships.

Expanded Polystyrene (EPS) significantly contributes to sustainability through its environmental benefits and efficiency in reducing assembly and distribution costs. Its use in packaging minimizes product damage, leading to fewer resources spent on remanufacturing and disposal. NexKemia is investing heavily in research and development to innovate and lessen EPS’s carbon footprint, underscoring a deep commitment to environmental improvement.

Our Promise

At Extreme Window and Entrance Systems, we believe that your windows, like your home, should be a reflection of your life. It’s why we build them here in Atlantic Canada, with our challenging climate in mind. It’s why our team of experienced craftsmen use the best materials to build them to the highest of standards, Energy Star© certified to ensure long-lasting comfort and environmentally sound insulating power. And it’s why we offer the widest range of customization choices and designs, to ensure that your windows and entrance systems fit your home perfectly, inside and out.

Our Inspiration

Standing at the window and watching your children build a snowman. Enjoying the rush of fresh, fragrant air as you open the window after a summer sun shower. Savouring the feeling of relief and anticipation as you look out and see your family pulling in the driveway. Our home is where we spend our most precious moments – our sanctuary, our inspiration. And while we often enjoy the enveloping embrace of friends and family, our home also offers the unique opportunity to bring the outdoors in, and to enjoy the warmth and beauty of nature from our own vantage point.

Jokey - your global partner for packaging solutions

High-quality plastic packaging for food and non-food.

Jokey is a leading international manufacturer of rigid plastic packaging with lids. We produce plastic buckets, plastic tubs, plastic boxes and plastic trays by injection moulding. We offer food and non-food producers sophisticated, industry-specific packaging solutions.

Packaging from Jokey stands for top quality, hygiene, user-friendliness and innovation. Our standard range includes round, rectangular, square and oval plastic packaging from 120 ml to 35 l. Our buckets, tubs and trays are 100% recyclable in the recycling cycle. From the resulting secondary raw materials we produce environmentally friendly packaging for non-food products.

For 55 years, the name Jokey has stood for outstanding know-how in plastic injection moulding and customer-oriented service. With 2,300 employees, we produce in 16 plants in 13 countries and supply customers in around 80 countries. Our own tool manufacturing company, a division for technical plastic parts, and our high-quality bathroom furniture range round off our plastics competence.

As Your Injection Molding Supplier…

The team at Custom Plastics International Limited will take injection molded plastics out of your supply chain issues! Conveniently located outside of Toronto, Ontario, Custom Plastics International Limited is a privately owned Canadian custom injection molder with over 50 years experience molding precision thermoplastic products.  With our automated injection molding machinery ranging in size from 35 – 500 ton, Custom Plastics International Limited offers a low cost precision alternative to off-shore injection molding.

With our experienced team of plastic professionals coupled with solid local and off-shore tool builders, we have the ability to help ensure your plastic project is a success from the design/prototype stage to production.  At the front end of your project the engineers at Custom Plastics International Ltd have experience in all facets of plastic design including materials, part design, mold design, processing, fixture design, and metrology.  Our systems are defined and ready to manage 100’s of projects simultaneously.  We have the structure, methodology and discipline to break down the designs and provide the feedback for robust plastic design.  We do this quickly as we understand the need to get products to market.

Custom Plastics International Ltd save you money by either automating the production of your molded product or providing value added assembly during the machine cycle to optimize the production of your plastic projects.  We will provide you with a higher level plastic product at a reduced price; we are able to do this because we own our building, land and all of the equipment in our facility.  This combined with our efficient operations give you a competitive supply with increased value & support that you can’t get from the other side of the World.  Our vast global customer/supply base and flexible systems driven processes allow us to easily adapt to all quality/business requirements supporting companies ranging from start-up to global contract manufacturers.

MANUFACTURIER DE FILMS SOUFFLÉS EN POLYÉTHYLÈNE

Votre partenaire pour des films performants et écoresponsables.

45 ANS D’INNOVATION ET D’EXPERTISE CHEZ POLYEXPERT

Depuis 1979, nous développons des solutions d’emballage innovantes et performantes, adaptées aux besoins spécifiques de l’agroalimentaire et du secteur industriel. Nos films recyclables faits sur mesure allient fiabilité et respect de l’environnement, affirmant notre engagement pour un avenir durable.

Voir nos technologies
NOS MARCHÉS
ALIMENTAIRE
NON ALIMENTAIRE
FILMS POUR CONVERTISSEUR
AGRICULTURE
NOTRE VISION ÉCORESPONSABLE

Certifié ÉCORESPONSABLE par Ecocert Canada, PolyExpert a à cœur la diminution de son empreinte écologique, l’utilisation responsable des ressources et le développement durable. Au fil des ans, plusieurs initiatives ont été mises en place dans cet optique de développement durable et d’amélioration continue. Nous avons entre autres développé des pellicules biodégradables et compostables et des pellicules mono-matériau pour permettre le recyclage des emballages flexibles.

Au quotidien, nous prônons et adoptons des pratiques responsables et nous affirmons notre position par des actions concrètes et judicieuses, autant dans la fabrication de nos pellicules que dans la gestion de nos activités quotidiennes (récupération et réutilisation des retailles issues de notre production, revalorisation du matériel informatique obsolète par une entreprise spécialisée, installation de bornes de recharge pour voitures électriques, etc.).

Découvrir nos initiatives en développement durable
À PROPOS DE NOUS

Chef de file canadien, PolyExpert est une entreprise entièrement dédiée à l'extrusion de film de polyéthylène par procédé de soufflage. Grâce à notre approche personnalisée, nous trouvons des solutions innovantes, efficaces et durables. Nous offrons aujourd'hui plus de 150 pellicules différentes.

Découvrir PolyExpert
NOS FILMS AGRICOLES

Nous fabriquons plusieurs films de polyéthylène biodégradables et conventionnels consacrés à l'agriculture. Efficaces pour le contrôle des mauvaises herbes, l'augmentation du rendement des cultures, le contrôle de l'humidité et plus encore, ces pellicules vous feront économiser temps et efforts.

Explorer nos produits agricoles
NOS EXPERTISES
Technologies

Nos pellicules de polyéthylène sont le produit d’un usinage avancé. Elles sont utilisées dans des emballages alimentaires et non alimentaires, dans des films agricoles et industriels. Nous sommes particulièrement fiers de nos films biodégradables et compostables.

En savoir plus
Laboratoire

Nous sommes fiers de disposer de notre propre laboratoire et d’équipements à la fine pointe de la technologie. Chaque lot produit est assidûment testé afin d’en assurer la qualité irréprochable. Nous ne visons rien de moins que l’excellence.

En savoir plus
Approche

La satisfaction de nos clients est notre priorité. De la prise de votre commande à son exécution puis sa livraison, nous mettons tout en œuvre pour satisfaire vos exigences et dépasser vos attentes. PolyExpert souhaite devenir un partenaire de votre réussite.

En savoir plus
Savoir-faire

Notre équipe d’experts développe des solutions novatrices et efficaces pour répondre à vos besoins spécifiques. Si nos pellicules de polyéthylène ne répondent pas à vos besoins spécifiques, nous n’hésiterons pas à en créer une sur mesure. Chimistes, ingénieurs, techniciens et opérateurs d’expérience sont à votre service!

En savoir plus
COMMENT POUVONS-NOUS VOUS AIDER?

Quels que soient vos besoins en matière de film plastique, PolyExpert est là!

Dites-nous ce que vous cherchez et nous vous contacterons rapidement avec des solutions adaptées à votre réalité, votre délai et votre budget.

SPECIALTY TOOL & MANUFACTURING COMPANY
OUR SERVICES

S
TAMCO Specialty Tool and Manufacturing Company is a one-stop shop offering turnkey manufacturing and repair solutions to a variety of industries throughout Canada and around the world.

Founded in 1949, our business model has been to consistently exceed our customer’s expectations with on time delivery and high quality products. By investing in our people through training and mentorship, we strive to motivate and maintain the highest caliber of employees in a proud, safe and good working environment. With a large variety of equipment we can offer fast service, competitive pricing and be the complete solution to our customer’s needs and expectations.

With over 65 years of experience in design development, 3-D modeling, reverse-designing and drafting combined; STAMCO can offer its customers a variety of services. We use advanced software such as Solidworks, AutoCAD, and Flow software for programming design solutions. We strive to always be consistent with our ability to innovate and improve the quality and manufacturability of what we design. STAMCO has a solid team of design specialists and machinists dedicated to providing our customers with many solutions for their entire product and tool needs. This includes crafting the idea and design conception, all the way through models and drawings, to the shop floor in manufacturing.

STAMCO is always growing and advancing forward in the design of manufactured tools: these tools include molds (plastic, rubber, styrofoam, or urethane), dies and parts for a variety of industries made of steel, other metals, plastic, or many more materials.

Our sectors of work include Oil and Gas, and countless other industries including Utilities, Transportation, replacement equipment parts in Food and Industrial equipment, plus the City of Edmonton and the University of Alberta. Our goal is to provide excellent service the customer can count on. We have the ability and the people to provide our customers with the services they require and we meet or exceed those expectations.

Email: info@stamcotool.com

Alimentation, ameublement, articles de sport, construction, fenestration, médical, portes de garage, portes résidentielles et commerciales, présentoirs, rampes et plus encore…Notre équipe de conception met toutes ces années d’expertise et de recherche et de développement pour répondre aux besoins de notre clientèle. Nous avons notre propre atelier d’usinage qui nous permet de réaliser nos matrices à faible coût.

MATIÈRES PREMIÈRES

De plus, nous avons un très large choix de couleurs; en exemple, nous avons plus de 10 blancs différents en inventaire. Il est aussi possible de choisir votre couleur « sur mesure ».

PVC rigide, PVC flexible, PVC poudre, Polypropylène, Polyéthylène, TPE et autres polymères.

Nous avons notre propre atelier d’usinage qui nous permet de réaliser nos matrices à faible coût. Poly Bag Supplier – Custom Flexible 
Packaging Solution Provider
Full-Service Solutions Throughout North America

Polynova is a comprehensive flexible packaging solution provider producing a wide range of plastic bag and films. As a leading poly bag supplier serving the Canadian and US markets since 1981, we deliver customized, high quality print solutions for plastic bags, pouches and other packaging options. When you need a poly bag or pouch that is practical, affordable and does justice to your product and brand image, Polynova is your best choice.

Quick turnaround and unbeatable quality coupled with excellent customer service is why customers depend on us as their custom flexible packaging solution provider.

Headquartered in Richmond, BC, Canada, our strategic South-Western location helps us reach out and cater to the needs of our customers across Canada and the USA.

All our product lines are manufactured upon custom specification. Years of manufacturing have helped us master the poly bag technology to ensure that our customers have the required flexibility to combine the properties of different product groups. For example, a full-colour high quality print handle bag can be ordered in both, bio-degradable or reusable form. Or, a temper proof bag can be made of any type of coex, or laminated film. We can supply a very wide range of PE and PP materials from LDPE, HDPE, CPE, PPE, PP, OPP, or PVC, to non-woven cloth or biodegradable material.

The number of choices and variations are literally infinite; you only have to tell us what you need and we’ll deliver!

Welcome to Onward Plastics, formerly known as Onward Cluthé Hardware Products. We are a custom plastic injection moulding company located in Kitchener, Ontario, Canada. We can assist you from your product design and tool build, through to part production and shipping logistics. Founded in 1939, we continue to grow, automate, and expand our operation. In 2021, we finalized the acquisition of Webplas Inc in Waterloo, Ontario, which added additional expertise and enhanced capabilities in plastic manufacturing to our organization. In 2024, we merged Onward Cluthe and Webplas into Onward Plastics.
Onward Plastics is a family business committed to the safety of our employees, and the quality of the products that we produce. We can handle your high volume production of large and small parts! Keep reading to learn more, and reach out with questions on how we can help you!
CUSTOM INJECTION MOULDING

We have 44 injection moulding presses ranging in size from 39 tons to 1750 tons. We can assist you with your part design, mould sourcing, material selection, part assembly, packaging, and your high volume production requirements.

QUALITY

Our quality is our reputation and we strive to meet or exceed your quality requirements. Our Quality Management System is ISO 9001:2015 certified, and all of our staff complete our quality training program.

PROPRIETARY PRODUCTS

Where our moulding all began!
We have a wide selection of heavy duty measuring containers, funnels, oilers, scoops, furniture glides, and handle grips for your industrial needs.

WHY US

We're manufacturers too. We've been in business since 1906 and understand the importance that each part has on your production line and meeting your quality expectations. We are committed to our clients and know that our production can impact your brand.

Enhance your brand image and marketing by maximizing visibility/impact of your packaging by advertising your store name, products, and brand logo on a Custom Retail Bag or packaging. Customized retail packagings are a perfect fit for your retail marketing strategy.

MATERIAL HANDLING

JUNISE has a wide variety of styles of bags that are fully customizable to help you protect your products during their storage or transport. Whether your needs are for bulk packaging for transport, or individual mailers for sending small parcels, we can offer you fully customizable solutions to help ease the shipping process, save costs, and enhance your brand image and marketing by maximizing visibility/impact of your packaging.

Open Bags

A term that refers to any bag or packaging that is closed on 3 sides, and open either at the top or bottom of the bag to be loaded with product. These are the most widely used bags and packagings in the industry.


Closeable Bags

Closeable bags are similar to open bags. It refers to any bag or packaging that is closed on 3 sides, and on the open side, either at the top or bottom of the bag, some type of attachment (zip, tape, draws string, etc…) is inserted in order to close the bag shut.


Roll Stock

The term roll stock is used to refer to any flexible packaging material or style that is in a roll form (sheeting, U-Film, J-Film, C-Film, etc…). This form of packaging is typically used in line with semi-automated or automated packaging equipment, to directly package the final product.

Who We Are
Zero waste packaging shows a significant cost savings compared to disposable.


Over 18 years ago CkdPack was born out of a simple belief that packaging did not have to be expendable. We are not satisfied until you are satisfied, and we will go to great lengths to ensure the protection of your goods.
 
Our focus is to guarantee that your product is packed to perfection-whether it be in a container, rack, or bin-using our reusable systems.
 
Our engineers know how to secure your cargo for shipping or storage. Ckdpack, always at your service 100% of the time.
 
Our unique approach to packaging starts at the very beginning. By involving our Team in the early development of your project, we can help integrate logistical considerations into your timeline and budget.
 
We can show you how different options in packaging can impact the success of your program. By getting a grasp on these issues from the beginning, we will save you time and money.

Thermoforming is the process of heating and forming a variety of modern plastic materials into useful packaging solutions such as blisters packs, clamshells, disposable trays and insert trays, as well as colorful counter and retail floor displays. At Propak Plastics we work closely with our customers at every step of the design, tooling and production process to ensure the most cost effective solution to their packaging and display requirements.

Established in 1979, Propak Plastics manufactures custom designed vacuum thermoformed plastic products in a variety of materials, styles, colors and finishes for the pharmaceutical, cosmetic, hardware, electronics, sporting goods industries and many more. Our extensive facilities provide us with the flexibility to manufacture large or small production quantities. Other services include CNC routing, ultrasonic sealing, custom fulfillment, hot stamping, silk screening, assembly and heat bending.

We offer:

Highly competitive tooling and unit pricing

Innovative package design and creative tooling options

A wide range of automated, high volume production machinery

Low cost, manual assembly capabilities and post production sealing equipment to meet your special product assembly or package fulfillment requirements

High quality production and services at the lowest possible price

Molding Ideas That Matter.
Custom injection molded solutions.

Since 1945 we’ve been quietly building a reputation as one of North America’s most innovative and reliable custom injection molding companies. From concept, through design for manufacture and engineering review right through to delivering the final product, we inject quality, stability, practicality and value into every stage of the process.

GET IN TOUCH
Why Us

We’ve invested in state-of-the-art technology in our 50,000 square foot facility with ISO Class 7 Clean Room and in house tool room. More importantly, we’ve invested in the people with the experience, passion, knowhow and creativity to ensure your project is delivered exactly when and where you need it. We do everything in our power to keep you informed on every aspect of the process, so it is like working with a trusted friend. With us, it is a partnership and we will always be direct.

ABOUT US
How We Work
DESIGN

We take a collaborative approach to Design for Manufacture and custom manufacturing solutions, bringing decades of experience and practical problem solving to identify any possible flaws that may affect your project before launch.

TROUBLESHOOT

We have a long history of customers bringing us problems other molders or offshore suppliers can’t solve. We pride ourselves at reviewing every option to ensure the right solution is chosen for your product’s longevity.

MANUFACTURE

Whether it is a high volume odometer needle, a fully assembled seed meter or a sterile cell culture plate, we can produce products for any industry and often times products that others refuse.

GEOTUBE

GEOTUBE® dewatering containers are an effective dewatering technology fabricated from a specially engineered geotextile which provides confinement of the fine solids inside the container, while allowing water to permeate through the engineered geotextile. As the water drains, the solids continue to densify and consolidate over time. Once the solids are fully consolidated or have met minimum requirements for transport, several options are available for disposal of the dewatered material.

Who We Are

Firwin Corporation is a leading manufacturer of custom insulation products for diesel and gas engines & exhaust systems, and industrial applications. Our 2 main product lines are removable and reusable insulation blankets (also known as removable insulation covers and removable insulation jackets) and permanent Hard Coat™ composite insulation. We also stock a wide range of off-the-shelf high temperature tapes and sleeves.

À PROPOS DE VERSAPROFILES
Carrières

Nous offrons des possibilités de carrières dans plusieurs domaines ainsi qu’un environnement de travail stimulant. Notre équipe est toujours à la recherche de personnes impliquées voulant relever de nouveaux défis et ayant soif d’apprendre. Joignez-vous à une équipe accueillante et audacieuse!

EN SAVOIR +
Actualités
Versaprofiles était présent au « Building Energy Boston » 2024!

Organisée par le Northeast Sustainable Energy Association, l’objectif de cette conférence de 5 jours est d’échanger avec la communauté d’architectes, d’ingénieurs, et de promoteurs immobiliers sur les tendances et progrès en développement durable et en électrification des bâtiments. Très enrichissant et pertinent comme événement, pour lequel notre collègue Jean-François Lavoie ing. MBA était sur place afin de mettre en évidence les avantages de la géothermie, et de représenter notre entreprise dans le cadre d’une mission économique organisée par Québec International!

2 nouveaux silos à St-Lazare

Nous avons récemment remplacé deux de nos silos dans lesquels nous entreposons la matière première avec laquelle nous produisons nos tuyaux, soit le polyéthylène en granules.

Changer d’aussi gros silos n’est pas une mince affaire et nécessite une logistique hors pair. Cet exercice se veut toutefois nécessaire afin d’alimenter en continu 24/24 nos procédés d’extrusion et de répondre aux normes de sécurité et aux réglementations en vigueur. Ainsi, les risques de contamination des procédés se voient grandement diminués. Et on ne se le cachera pas, ces nouveaux silos sont visuellement beaucoup plus attrayants, ce qui améliore l’impact visuel pour le voisinage!

Fabriqués en tôle ondulée, les 2 nouveaux silos présentent chacun un volume de 3 639 pieds cubes, et peuvent accueillir jusqu’à 60 000 kg de granules de polyéthylène.

Merci à notre partenaire Les Entreprises REL pour les silos et merci à notre collègue Ghazi Mhadhbi pour le tournage et montage de cette vidéo fort impressionnante!

Versaprofiles souligne ses 10 ans à Sainte-Claire

La pandémie nous aura peut-être empêché de célébrer notre 10e anniversaire à la date prévue, mais nous nous sommes repris en force 1 an plus tard! Nous avons réuni nos 80 employés, tout souriants, à notre usine de Ste-Claire, question d’inaugurer l’agrandissement de celle-ci, et célébrer notre succès et le plaisir d’être tous ensemble. Méchoui, jeux gonflables et tournoi de mini-putt étaient au rendez-vous!

EN SAVOIR +

UNRIVALED CUSTOMER SERVICE & SUPPORT

We consider every client as a partner in our business, and us in yours! For complete customer support you can trust us to be there from order entry to delivery. You can expect exceptional one-on-one client support, timely deliveries, customized solutions, quality & consistent products, and flexible order options!

Whether it's a small batch or a large order, Copol is committed to making sure your product is delivered as quickly as possible.

In most cases, we can fill & deliver an order WITHIN 3 WEEKS of receiving it!

PRODUCT QUALITY IS A GUARANTEE

Simply put, if you're not happy with your order - we'll always make it right. When it comes to safety, with our HACCP Certification and internal quality testing, you can rest assured that your products will always meet the highest standards. Check out our latest HACCP audit

WE TAKE CARE OF OUR ENVIRONEMENT

At Copol we take our environmental responsibility very seriously. Not a single ounce of our product is sent to waste. Excess film is re-pelletized and recycled back into our production line. Once complete, all our films are recyclable in the PP recycle streams (number 5).

NEWS & HIGHLIGHTS FROM COPOL

The Circular Economy

The future for the planet depends on recycling our raw materials, creating the Circular Economy.

That is the direction of the plastic industry to ensure the optimum use of our packaging materials without negatively impacting our environment.

The intent is to reap the many benefits of plastic packaging such as:

Smaller carbon footprint than other packaging options such as paper, glass or metal
Better protection of food products resulting in less food waste
More availability of food products worldwide

without the burden of plastic waste building up in the environment.

We need to make it easier to recycle plastic packaging. Mixed plastics do not lend themselves well to recycling and some plastics are very difficult to recycle.

PP is one of the most easily and widely recycled plastics and offer many advantages.

So consider using an all PP structure and help boost the Circular Economy and help the environment. All our products are recyclable in the PP recycle stream number 5.

Sacs d'échantillonnage stériles

Les sacs d’échantillonnage stériles de LABPLAS sont des récipients souples et sécuritaires assurant des résultats d’analyse fiables. Ils sont l’outil idéal pour toute activité de prélèvement!

Biohazard

Le sac Biohazard est conçu pour le transport de matières dangereuses et est doté d’un système de fermeture permettant à l’utilisateur une fermeture étanche et sécuritaire.

Twirl'Opaque

Le Twirl'Opaque est conçu pour protéger les échantillons photosensibles. Sa résine noire constitue une barrière contre la lumière protégeant ainsi l’intégrité de certaines substances sensibles à la lumière.

Twirl'Blue

Le Twirl’Blue, grâce à sa couleur bleue, est facilement repérable pour éviter d’éventuelles contaminations par corps étranger. Il est l'outil indispensable pour l'industrie agroalimentaire.

Autoportant

Le sac Autoportant est idéal lorsque vos deux mains sont requises ailleurs. Il peut rester debout sans avoir recourt à aucun support ce qui facilite et accélère le processus d’analyse.

Filtra Bag

Le Filtra Bag est un sac stérile pour malaxeur avec filtre. Il a été conçu pour résister aux homogénéisateurs les plus robustes et pour faciliter la prise d’aliquote. La membrane filtre permet aux bactéries de circuler entre les compartiments tout en maintenant séparés les plus gros résidus

Secure-T

Le Secure-T est un sac stérile pour malaxeur, sans filtre. Il a été conçu pour résister aux homogénéisateurs les plus robustes. Idéal pour les tests en laboratoire, son ouverture détachable assure la stérilité jusqu'à l'utilisation.

Secure-Strip

Le Secure-Strip est une solution pratique et innovatrice offrant un accès rapide à nos sacs Secure-T grâce à un distributeur compact et sécuritaire.

Twirl'em

Le Twirl’em est un incontournable pour les professionnels de plusieurs industries. Son système de fermeture sécurisé intégré en fait une solution étanche et hermétique pour des résultats d’analyse fiables.

NOPA Twirl Bag

Le sac d’échantillonnage NOPA, spécialement conçu pour la National Oilseed Processors Association (NOPA), est idéal pour l’industrie des oléagineux. Grâce à son système de fermeture sécurisé, il préserve l’intégrité des échantillons et prévient toute contamination.

Voir Sacs d'échantillonnage stériles
Supports et outils complémentaires

Les supports LABPLAS vous permettent de garder sécuritairement en place vos sacs d’échantillons tandis que les différents outils complémentaires vous permettent de faciliter vos opérations quotidiennes. Découvrez comment nos accessoires simplifient l'utilisation de nos solutions de prélèvements!

Stylo détectable

Moulé en une seule pièce pour plus de sécurité dans l’environnement de l’usine, le Stylo détectable est fait de plastique imprégné de particules de métal, ce qui lui permet d’être repérer au détecteur de métal et visible aux rayons X.

Gants bleus stériles

Pratiques et sécuritaires, les Gants bleus stériles sont emballés en paire individuelle et pliés de manière qu'ils puissent être retirés du pochon, dépliés et enfilés sans que les doigts du gant n’aient été en contact avec l’utilisateur, réduisant ainsi les risques de contamination.

LABrack

Le LABrack, fait en acier inoxydable à 100%, est autoclavable, ce qui permet aux utilisateurs d’entrer le produit dans les milieux de travail hautement contrôlés et qui exigent un grand niveau de stérilité. Polyvalent et sécuritaire, il s'agit du support par excellence pour vos activités d'échantillonnage!

Dévidoir

Le dévidoir est très résistant et il sert de distributeur à notre rouleau Secure-strip qui contient 250 sacs. Il est compact, sécuritaire et peut entrer dans les laboratoires les plus stricts en matière de stérilité puisqu'il est autoclavable.

Support individuel

Solide et flexible, le Support individuel est conçu pour maintenir le sac ouvert à la position verticale afin de permettre à l’utilisateur d'avoir les mains libres durant ses opérations!

Barrette de fermeture

Conçue pour refermer les sacs sans système de fermeture intégré, la Barrette de fermeture de sacs d'échantillonnage assure une fermeture étanche et sécuritaire. Elle peut être utilisée de pair avec le LABrack et est offerte en différentes grandeurs pour combler tous vos besoins!

Rack'N'Lab

Pratique et polyvalent, le Rack’N’Lab est un support conçu pour faciliter le transport des sacs d’échantillonnage et le maintien des sacs à la verticale. Fait de polypropylène vierge, il est léger, robuste et idéal pour toutes vos activités d'échantillonnage, que ce soit sur le terrain ou en laboratoire!

Voir Supports et outils complémentaires
Trousses d'échantillonnage stériles

Les trousses d'échantillonnage stériles de LABPLAS sont des solutions tout-en-un vous permettant de simplifier vos activités en limitant le matériel à transporter sur le terrain!

Trousse d'échantillonnage d'eau

La Trousse d’échantillonnage d’eau, avec son comprimé de thiosulfate de sodium intégré, est conçue pour le prélèvement, le transport et l’analyse d’échantillons d’eau chlorée ou non-chlorée dans des conditions d’asepsie.

Sani-Sponge

Le Sani-Sponge est conçu pour le prélèvement des échantillons utilisés pour détecter les contaminants microbiologiques et autres pathogènes alimentaires présents sur les diverses surfaces de préparation.

Sani-Stick

Le Sani-Stick, avec son manche rigide, est conçu pour faciliter le prélèvement des échantillons utilisés pour détecter des contaminants microbiologiques et autres pathogènes alimentaires.

Wipa-Boots

Les Wipa-Boots sont conçues pour l’échantillonnage de surfaces au sol. Elles permettent la prévention, le contrôle et la détection de différents types de pathogènes.

Sani-S'wipe

Le Sani-S'wipe est une trousse comprenant une chiffonnette bleue et un sac stérile. Elle est spécialement conçue pour prélever des échantillons afin de détecter la présence de contaminants microbiologiques et autres pathogènes alimentaires sur diverses surfaces.

EnrichPod

La trousse EnrichPod est constituée d'un sac pour homogénéisateur contenant un milieu de culture déshydraté et pré-dosé qui permet aux laboratoires d’être plus efficaces.

POURQUOI CHOISIR
LE POLYMÈRE?

Dans le domaine des armoires de cuisine et du design intérieur, aucune matière n’offre plus de possibilités que le polymère. Et aucune ne facilite autant le travail des designers et cuisinistes. Le polymère rend l’audace possible tout offrant des options idéales pour les pièces nécessitant un nettoyage fréquent. La souplesse de personnalisation des panneaux de polymère et l’immense variété de couleurs, finis et textures ouvrent la voie à n’importe quel style architectural.

Actuel. Audacieux.

L’offre de produits à base de polymère est en soi une source d’inspiration. Le développement y est avant-gardiste et connecté aux nouvelles tendances en matière de stylisme.

Impeccable. Uniforme.

Le polymère permet d’obtenir une apparence parfaite, sans aucune traînée ou variation de couleur. Le niveau d'uniformité du fini est inégalé, de l’ultra-mat à l’ultra-lustré.

Résistant. Durable.

En plus d’offrir une excellente résistance à l’humidité, le polymère permet une fabrication sans aucun joint. Sa surface nécessite peu d’entretien et est facile à nettoyer.

Matière recyclable

Le polymère contient des matières recyclées et recyclables. Les avancées technologiques permettront bientôt d’atteindre une proportion de matières recyclables de près de 100 %.

What Makes MPI Papermills Different?

Why Family Ownership Matters

MPI Papermills is proud to be family owned since 1975. Our family values have influenced the type of business we have built, for the better of our clients, and for the environment. 

As a Family owned and operated company, we care about our business relationships the way we do our family. 

At MPI Papermills, we foster values of entrepreneurship, loyalty, accountability, safety and commitment to the environment. MPI Papermills has built a flat hierarchical structure, which means you have access to the right people when you need them. This also means our team is responsive to your needs resulting in quick decision making.

Faster decision making, in combination with our commitment to our clients, ensures that your business moves as quickly as we do.

Why MPI

At MPI, we believe in a safe environment for our employees and a healthy environment for our children. 

By recycling and using recycled materials in our paper, we reduce the amount of waste that has traditionally gone to landfill. Our investment in our water treatment facility reduces our water consumption dramatically. And, by utilizing pre- and post-consumer fibres, trees can be saved by the thousands.

We are constantly searching for energy efficiency within our manufacturing processes, in keeping with our commitment to these values.

ABOUT US

Since 1975, Oakmont Industries has been supplying wood, steel and glass doors, specialties and professional hardware to multi-family residential and mixed-use projects in BC, Alberta and along the West Coast of the United States. Our vast experience supplying thousands of projects of all different sizes, geographies and complexity gives our customers the piece of mind that Oakmont’s scope of work will be executed to the highest standard.

Oakmont prides itself on the quality and reputation of our customer base, as well as the duration of the relationships we enjoy with them. We measure our success solely by our ability to continually earn our customers trust by supplying their projects year after year.

Oakmont operates out of a purpose built 48,000 sq. ft. facility in Port Kells, Surrey. It houses our wood shop, steel welding shop and glass shop.  Oakmont carries substantial on-hand inventory for all three shops at all times.

WHAT MAKES US UNIQUE
SINGLE POINT OF CONTACT

Each customer’s project has a single point of contact at Oakmont from the quoting process right through to when the last product is shipped to site and the building is complete.  This continuity allows Oakmont’s Project Managers to become intimately familiar with the unique aspects of every project and gives our customers peace of mind that they know exactly who to call to get the answer they are looking for.

WE DO NOT OUTSOURCE

Our philosophy is that if we are to supply a quality product on time to our customers, then we need to control as much of the process as possible.

Oakmont buys raw materials from reputable manufacturers; assembles the finished product in our own wood, steel and glass shops, with our own people and equipment and delivers to site on our own fleet of trucks. This control reduces problems on your jobsite and allows for an extremely rapid response in the event a problem does arise.

WE ANTICIPATE THE CONSTRUCTION SCHEDULE

Oakmont is focused only on supplying multi-family residential and mixed-use projects that have a residential component. This focus, combined with decades of experience, allows our Project Managers to know how a building is built and how our scope fits into that schedule.  Our Project Managers are always anticipating what will be needed 6 to 12 weeks ahead of time to ensure the site has what is needed, when its needed.

WE ARE COMMITTED TO TECHNOLOGY

Oakmont is committed to continuous investment in technology. Our commitment extends to all facets of the business from manufacturing, sales, operations and finance. All our investments are focused on improving Oakmont’s service levels of our on-site customers.

CAREERS

Interested in joining the Oakmont team? Check out our open positions and send your resume if you qualify. If there are no open positions listed below, you should still send us your resume because we’re always keen to meet talented people who could be a fit in the future. We appreciate you taking the time to apply, but we aren’t able to respond to every submission.

 In House Tool Room

Our full service in house toolroom is run by skilled mold makers and technicians with decades of experience and ensure that your molds are well maintained and yield their maximum capacity, allowing for minimal downtime, high precision, and quick turnarounds. We also provide no cost tool maintenance and service options where we design and build the molds.

Mold Flow Analysis

Through our advanced mold flow analysis modeling, we can simulate material flow into and through a mold to create optimal conditions for production. This predictive method allows for corrective action before mold production begins, saving time and cost. Our design team will work with you to maximize part performance and minimize tooling costs.

Design Expertise

From start to finish, Centennial will work with you to clearly understand your part’s intended usage and all of the key considerations and design tooling and processes that will meet your exact specifications and needs, regardless of how simple or complex.

WELCOME TO
PROTECTOLITE™ COMPOSITES INC.
Protectolite™ Composites Inc. is a pioneer in the field of molded reinforced thermoset composites. For over 70 years, we have provided our clients with optimum designs, processes and materials that meet their performance and budget requirements.

Protectolite™ Composites Inc. combines fiberglass, carbon, aramid and other reinforcing materials with polyester, epoxy, phenolic and other resins to manufacture PROTECTive and LighT – Protectolite™ composites that meet and exceed industry standards.




Protectolite™ Composites Inc. is the registered trademark for the FRP – Fiberglass Reinforced Plastics "Composite" developed by Protectolite™. Our unique specialty is our ability to manufacture solid, homogeneous one-piece composite moldings of electrical & corrosion-grade sheets with thicknesses ranging from 1/32" to 6.00".




Unmatched quality, timely delivery and competitive prices are the cornerstones of the company’s vision. From providing superior electrical insulation, weight savings, and cost savings to corrosion resistance, structural strength, and temperature control, we offer composite solutions that are built to last.

FOUR KEY SUCCESS CRITERIA IN COMPOSITE MANUFACTURING
The quality and durability of our products are a result of our strict adherence to the four criteria our manufacturing process is based on:
READ MORE
MECHANICAL STRENGTH
Based largely on type, amount and arrangement of the fiber reinforcement and of the different types of fibers, aramid, carbon, thermoplastic or fiberglass.
CHEMICAL, ELECTRICAL, AND THERMAL PERFORMANCE
Based on the type of resin used and how it is combined with other components. We determine and deliver the levels of performance required by your industry’s standards.
MATERIAL SELECTION
Material selection alongside product and tool design determines the selection of the optimal process technology. The type of material used plays a crucial role in tool design and in determining which process to use.
COST PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS
Cost and benefits are weighed, and the final decision is made based on the client’s input, our feedback, and the client's careful consideration of the final options we present to them.

WELCOME TO LEGEND

Legend Rubber Inc. was established in 2004 and has grown
to become the leader in rubber cow comfort products in North America.

When it comes to the perfect solution for your cow comfort and cow welfare, look no further than Legend Rubber. We have a full range of quality, walkway mats, cow beds and slat mats made from durable rubber. These are specially engineered not only to be tough, withstanding everything farm life can throw at them, but they offer stability, comfort and protection for your valuable dairy herd. This helps to ensure a restful and stress-free environment, crucial for a happy herd to maintain optimum productivity levels while reducing the risk of injury to not only your animals but your staff as well.

With over 15 years of experience in the dairy industry, we have become the leader in cow comfort rubber products throughout North America. Our expertise includes valuable experience gained in the UK over the course of 8 years before establishing our operation in Canada. Here, we completed thousands of projects on dairy farms across the UK and New Zealand which has enabled us to build on that experience with our North American operations. No matter how small or large your dairy farm, we focus on solutions that will increase the comfort levels of your dairy herd, boosting productivity and lowering the chance of injury to both animals and staff.

Why choose legend?

Legend Rubber manufactures top quality rubber products in Ontario Canada. This is backed up with an excellent after sales service. Our Certified Dealer network is extensive in Canada and continues to grow in the United States, New Zealand and the United Kingdom.

Anti-Slip Surfaces

Recent research shows 30% of lactating cows in the North American dairy herd are clinically lame. Our anti-slip surfaces assist in maintaining cow mobility and also to prevent injury that could result in loss of productivity or a potential cull due to the injury.

Strength and Comfort

Cows demonstrate a definite preference for the Legend Super Bed and Legend Softbed over crumb-filled mattresses, sand and liquid-filled beds. Given the choice, 80% of cows preferred to walk on rubber. Our mats are designed to provide your herd with greater comfort for optimum herd care.

Healthier Cows

Estimated costs of claw disease are up as high as $600 per case, taking into consideration treatment costs, follow up, lower yields, reduced reproduction performance, higher involuntary culling rates, discarded milk and the additional management effort required to care for lame cows.

Easy to Clean

Our rubber matting products are designed for easy upkeep, ensuring a clean and hygienic environment for both you and your cattle with minimal effort. Trusted by our dairy and beef farmer clients, our mats are praised for their quick and efficient cleaning capacity, and for keeping operations running smoothly.

Better Grip. Better Hooves. Better COWS.

À Propos
Les Plastiques FOLIA Inc. est une entreprise fondé en 2006 qui se spécialisé dans l'extrusion de résines thermoplastiques sur mesure, principalement dans les feuilles de plastique rigide et produits co-extrudés pour un large éventail de marchés.

Réduire notre empreinte écologique nous tiens à cœur.
Chaque année, nous utilisons plus de 2 millions de kilos de plastique recyclé dans nos produits.

Nous déménageons au courant de l'année 2024 dans une superficie de plus de 60 000 pieds carrés et en profitons pour mettre nos lignes de production à la fine pointe de la technologie.

THE ART OF PLACEMENT

Our Salesman know what designing a room is all about. Using their experience implementing custom built cabinets to suit a room, you will be astonished at the outcome. Instantly, that creative space your home receives will make you proud from the improved flow that transforms a room into a home. Spend a free consultation with our salesman, and visualize the space with cabinets from our 3D drawings. Have an idea, we can build it. Need some help, our salesman are here to listen to your needs and provide solutions.

Let Us Help
CABINET POSSIBILITIES

Thought about having cabinets in your kitchen, of course. Bathroom, of course. But how about cabinets in your children's bedrooms to make a permanent desk area. Or how about a makeup table and cabinets for a special girl or woman in the house. Did you consider seeing us for cabinets to complete your closet organization? We also can help you with a wet bar for the basement or entertaining area. How about cabinets to complement your fireplace area or ask a salesman about mantles and other shelving we specialize in.

Let Us Help
WINDOWS AND DOORS

Tired of that cold draft coming from your old metal slider windows. Do you want to replace those wood windows that came with the home but require constant upkeep with painting or finishing. Do you want a larger window where there is a small one now? We also specialize in replacing sealed units/glass units that may have been broken or just seem to fog up on you all the time between the panes of glass. Changing your siding and adding insulation on the exterior of your house - we know just what to manufacture for your needs.

Let Us Help

CABINETS

A kitchen like this will last for at least 20 years. For the sake of quality, we prefer to have control over every stage of the process – Ashly's Assurance: Manufacturers of Quality.

Our passion for building kitchens began over 25 years, and we know what’s important: first-rate materials, skilled craftsmen, technical precision. We inspect every stage of an Ashly branded kitchen, from the start to final assembly, making sure you receive our quality.

COUNTERTOPS

There are several choices to make when choosing your new countertop from Ashly's. We supply many styles of inexpensive laminate tops, or you can choose to have us install Granite or Quartz tops.

We sell only the best quality of tops. Even our less expensive laminate tops are backed with an incredible warranty. Maybe you are desiring an under mount sink, we have many to choose from, and make the process simple by looking after the plumbing.

WINDOWS

PVC windows are extremely durable and long lasting. PVC windows are available in several different types include sliding, awning, casement, picture, bay and combinations. PVC windows never need painting; they will not rot or warp like timber can; they will not corrode like metal windows can.

We also manufacture sealed units. Dual or Triple-Glazed; clear or Low-E coating; and filling the chamber with Argon are options we provide you.

DOORS

Exterior doors can enhance the look of your home and create a barrier from the external weather we experience in Saskatchewan. We offer many choices, including garden doors, patio, single hung, storm doors, and decorative glass or venting doors.

If you choose to have a fiberglass wood grain door that we pre-stain for your home, we can accommodate that choice for you. We stock a large assortment of weather stripping and door sweeps.

About Chantler Packages
The World of Packaging

Chantler Packages’ history goes back to 1930, when Ernest and John Chantler established a company, Chantler & Chantler, to sell innovative plastic products in Toronto, Canada.

The venture founded by the Chantler brothers eventually grew into a flexible packaging manufacturer located in Mississauga that specialized in packaging for the food industry. With national food brands as its customers, Chantler developed capabilities in film extrusion, flexographic printing, and high-speed bag making.

RIPPLEPAK:
TORONTO COMMERCIAL & RETAIL LEVEL PACKAGING EXPERTS

A division of Uthane Research Ltd, RipplePak Ltd. is a technology-oriented company based in Toronto that specializes in industrial packaging. The company was established by Mr. Ragui Ghali in 1976 with the objective to develop and to commercialize new technologies in the fields of packaging, insulation and plastic.

Smart Designs, State-Of-The-Art Products

At RipplePak, we believe that our continued success is due to our dedication to provide innovative, quality packaging and insulation products and professional services to our customers, including:

Moving supplies
Cold chain solutions
Packaging material
Insulapack Insulation

When you deal with RipplePak, we make it a point to enhance your products’ quality thanks in part to the best protection solutions designed for transport and storage. We offer a wide variety of packaging and shipping products and services that suit a countless number of applications.

The World of Packaging Supplies in Canada

RipplePak specializes in industrial packaging and has been around for decades to offer new and innovative solutions to the process of safely moving products. The company employs the touch of technology to handle every product’s specific design and needs expertly. It was founded by a chemical engineer whose expert knowledge of thermodynamics allowed him to come up with innovative methods of using the right raw materials for the most effective packaging solutions.

When moving items, the primary goal becomes its safe arrival to its destination. Often, even the most well-packed item can end up in pieces. Professional Packing Companies in Toronto work to ensure this is avoided by offering services that include packaging supplies in Canada. Whether the packed product will be shipped or stored, packing manufacturers offer every solution, from industrial packing supplies to cold chain solutions.

Custom Packaging

Custom packaging manufacturing companies offer solutions that help companies or individuals refer to a wide variety of styles, shapes, and packaging designs. Custom package manufacturing companies allow an individual or company to choose the kind of impression they would like their packaging to make. After all, before the product inside is revealed, the package makes the first impressions, and first impressions are thought to be the last impressions for a reason. Custom package manufacturing companies give way for individuality and creativity without sacrificing effectiveness and functionality.

Technology has allowed for a great number of innovative ways of packaging, including:

Bubble Wrap
Pabble Wrap
Die-Cut Foam Packaging
Corrugated U-Channels
Extra Heavy Duty Pabble Wrap
Corners and End Caps

Each offers its unique look, but most importantly, it promises varying ways and degrees of security depending on the product being packaged. It’s all about understanding the product that is being packaged.

Clôtures Frontenac

Un peu plus sur qui nous sommes

Fondé en 1998, Clôtures Frontenac est le leader en fabrication de clôtures ornementales en aluminium, rampe en aluminium et lattes pour clôtures "Frost".

Fier partenaire des contracteurs de clôtures, paysagistes, pisciniers, et bricoleurs, tous nos produits sont disponibles en vente directe ou à travers des distributeurs autorisés.

Les dirigeants de Clôtures Frontenac profitent de cette tribune pour remercier leurs fidèles employés qui, jour après jour entrent au travail avec le sourire ainsi que leurs clients et fournisseurs qui ont à coeur leur réussite.

We foster sustainable innovation by developing breakthrough BOPP, CPP and BOPLA packaging solutions that help protect products, avoid food waste, improve safety and hygiene, facilitate recycling processes and support a greener lifestyle.

Each product line is designed with the highest specifications, characteristics, and benefits, based on the organization’s best practices in product innovation and supply chain optimization.

Together we innovate
for future generations

Qui sommes-nous?

MobilFab est une entreprise basée dans le quartier de Pointe-aux-Trembles à Montréal. Ouverte en 2006, l’usine a fabriqué au-dessus de 3000 unités modulaires depuis son ouverture. Cette entreprise québécoise dessert l’ensemble des provinces et territoires du pays, assurant ainsi un service d’une qualité impeccable d’un océan à l’autre.

Forte de ses nombreuses années d’expérience dans le domaine de la fabrication de bâtiments préfabriqués et modulaires, MobilFab s’est dotée d’un département d’ingénierie pouvant concevoir une multitude de bâtiments préfabriqués, s’adaptant ainsi aux multiples besoins de l’industrie. L’entreprise possède de nombreuses certifications, la plus importante étant CSA 277-16, assurant un niveau de qualité supérieure pour tous ses produits.

Avec son usine d’une superficie de 55 000 pi2, MobilFab est équipée pour répondre à tous vos besoins de conception et de fabrication de bâtiments modulaires !

Notre mission

Être le chef de file de la conception et fabrication modulaire mobile.

"Choisir MobilFab, c’est choisir la qualité, la fiabilité et l’efficacité dans la fabrication de vos projets modulaires."
Pourquoi nous choisir?
Conception

Notre équipe d’ingénieurs s’adapte aux multiples besoins de sa clientèle en offrant des services de conception personnalisés. Certifiée CSA 277-16, MobilFab est reconnue pour la qualité et la polyvalence de ses fabrications. Desservant l’ensemble de provinces et territoires du Canada, MobilFab conçoit également en fonction des différents contextes géographiques.

Qualité

MobilFab vous assure une qualité exemplaire de la conception à la livraison. L’entreprise procède à une analyse rigoureuse de chaque produit afin de prévenir toute demande de retour ou de réparation. La satisfaction client est notre priorité!

Intégration

Notre équipe de professionnels qualifiés est intégrée et reconnue dans le réseau de fabrication de bâtiments modulaires pour sa fiabilité, sa rapidité et son efficacité. Notre équipe est orientée vers un objectif commun : votre satisfaction.

Les avantages MobilFab

L’agilité manufacturière dont fait preuve MobilFab se traduit en de courts délais de livraison, un tarif hyper-compétitif et une qualité irréprochable.

La compétitivité de MobilFab se joue à plusieurs niveaux. Nous visons l’excellence en vous offrant un produit de qualité supérieure et ce, dans des délais remarquables. Nos usines sont donc situées stratégiquement par rapport aux sites de livraison.

De plus, notre département d’ingénierie vous offre des services haut de gamme pouvant répondre à vos besoins de façon personnalisée.

CROWN PACKAGING
Crown Packaging Inc., a family-owned and operated company, takes pride in exceeding the expectations of our valued customers.

Established in 1986, we have diligently adhered to our prudent manufacturing philosophy from day one. With years of experience in the flexible packaging industry, we have not only built a reputable name for ourselves but have also earned the trust of our customers, while mastering the art of manufacturing. The integration of our accumulated knowledge over the years is evident in the way we conduct our business and manufacture our goods – reflecting in the superior quality of our final products. Our innovative approach, coupled with a strong work ethic, has not only allowed us to maintain excellence but has also fueled our growth within the packaging industry. At Crown Packaging Inc., we offer a diverse range of custom-made products that are meticulously designed in collaboration with our client. These products span through various fields of business, and various types of applications in the most logical and convenient manner. Our commitment to sustainability is reflected in our use of our eco-friendly materials, energy efficient processes and machinery, and controlling our emissions to ensure a responsible approach to manufacturing. Join us on our journey of delivering excellence since 1986, as we continue to evolve and innovate to meet the dynamic needs of our customers in the ever-changing world of packaging.

Who the “H” is “Humphrey”?


A “H”istory of Excellence
Humphrey is a Winnipeg based window and door manufacturer that has been satisfying customers in Western Canada for more than 50 years. We got our start when a group of window dealers combined in their search for higher quality windows and doors that could match the quality of their installations. The rest is a long history of excellence in designing, developing, manufacturing and supplying quality window and door products, built for the ever changing climate of the prairies.

Humphrey is focused on serving window and door professionals; renovators, contractors, glass shops, exterior specialists and discerning builders, looking for a product that will stand up and a manufacturer that will stand behind its products. Our warranties speak for themselves. We stand behind what we build. Tell me more…

“NXT Generation” Window and Door Systems

Humphrey “NXT Generation” window and door systems means a dedication to continual improvement in window and door design, quality and performance.

Humphrey windows and doors incorporate:

• The highest quality materials
• Tested and proven hardware
• The latest in energy efficient low-e glass and glass packages.
• Over fifty years of manufacturing experience
• Dedicated and accountable quality control process
• The latest technologies to enhance the performance of the glass, hardware, and operation of the window
Tell me more…

Made-to-Measure Precision

Every window is made to fit your exact specifications, can be fully customized to fit the design of your home or business, tested to exceed industry standards and based on precise measurements taken on-site by a Preferred Humphrey Dealer.

Quality Guarantee

Humphrey has developed its own unique and comprehensive quality control system, where through the use of state-of-the-art equipment, heavily researched and individually selected components, and favorable warranties has earned a reputation of providing outstanding value to our dealers and their customers. With thousands of windows and doors being shipped across Western Canada each year, Humphrey stands behind what we sell! Should something be found wrong in our product due to manufacturing error, or product defect, contact your “Preferred Humphrey Dealer” and they’ll take care of you. Tell me more…

Find A Dealer

Check out our map and find a dealer near you!

GET A QUOTE FROM A DEALER IN YOUR AREA


Preferred Dealer Advantage

We are focused on building quality products and providing responsive customer service through our network of “Preferred Humphrey Dealers”. Our list of “Window Professionals” across Western Canada have years of experience and the craftsmanship to ensure quality installations that can directly contribute to the overall performance of the finished product. When customers work with a Humphrey professional dealer they know they are working with some of the most experienced and trusted people in the business. In trusting them to take care of your window or door replacement, you have taken on a craftsman and a window professional dedicated to grow his or her business the old fashioned way one satisfied home owner at a time.

Our mission statement

“To provide the highest quality products, timely deliveries, friendly and responsive customer service, and exceptional value to our dealers and their customers!”

Greetings and welcome to Polyson!

We have been a family-run business for 32 years and counting, and have built a long-standing relationship for consistently high quality products, accommodating delivery times, friendly and personable service as well as competitive pricing.

A great testament to our ability to excel in the aforementioned areas is the fact that we have not had a website until our 27th year of business, and have relied solely on word of mouth from our loyal customers, some of whom have urged us to acquire a website! Please have a look around the website to see what products and services that we offer you, as well as what makes our company so unique.

Did you know?

The majority of polyethylene produced in North America is a by-product of natural gas – polyethylene is in fact derived from a waste product of the natural gas (used to heat our homes, etc.). The advent of a plastic has enabled this waste product to be redirected into a usable (and reusable) product instead of being burned (released) into the environment. In fact, most shopping bags (for example) are reused multiple times. Interestingly, plastic bags create only one third of the CO2 emissions than their paper counterparts, per-use. Further, according to a study commissioned by the U.K. Environment Agency in 2007, on a per-use basis, polyethylene shopping bags produce fewer carbon emissions than permanent, cloth bags, and were found to be only 0.5% as destructive to the climate as cloth bags on an average per-use basis.

THE CARDINAL I.G XL – EDGE SEALED UNITS

What makes Hometech’s Contour Series so aesthetically appealing is their classic Georgian architectural proportions. These beautiful ratios can be traced back to the brilliant aesthetic principles of the ancient Greeks who were masters of both beauty and design.
With sculpted proportioned lines, the Contour Series window offers the sophisticated elegance of finely crafted wood windows. These contoured surfaces play with the available light, finding attractive accents while eliminating the harsh reflected glare of flat surfaced windows.
We took our look one step further with advanced glazing technology, eliminating the need for exposed and unattractive black or white rubber glazing strips, common to virtually all other vinyl windows. The result is clean and attractive lines that will enhance the appearance of you home.
Now you can have both great street-side curb appeal and amazing elegant finished looks from the inside. A new and higher standard in style is finally here in a high performance vinyl window.

When the Heat Rises, Pelican Stays Cool: A Fire Survival Story

We recently received a remarkable tale from Don, a Pelican Customer from Alabama. It's a story that illustrates the resilience and exceptional performance of Pelican™ coolers in the face of extreme situations.

READ MORE 

Ice Storm No Match for Pelican 1510

In early February 2022 an ice storm came through my home town of Memphis which according to the NY Times caused around 60,000 people to lose power for almost a week. I was leaving for a work trip the next morning, so I had already packed the car in expectation to leave for my early flight. The storm hit and in addition to losing power, the accumulation of ice on the trees combined with high winds caused one of my neighbor's trees to fall directly on my SUV in the middle of the night.

READ MORE 

Crushproof and Crashproof

I was on my way home from teaching a women’s “stop the bleed” and firearms safety course at the Homestead (Florida) training center for Triad medical training. I had my Pelican 1615 Air Case tied down in the bed of my truck with my range setup inside. I was at a stoplight when I heard two cars coming up behind me at a high rate of speed. I realized they were coming into my lane and not stopping. The lead car struck the rear of my truck spinning me into the intersection and ejecting my Pelican Case from the bed of my truck. My Pelican Case ended up in the middle of the intersection and got dragged under a pickup truck, until it got run over and became dislodged. The gentleman who’s truck it was under noticed the case dislodge from under his truck and took it home. Historique

Intropak a été fondée dans le milieu des années 50 sous le nom de « Eastern Canada Packaging ». A l’origine établie à Richmond, Intropak a déménagé au cours des années 70 à Bromptonville sur la rue Laval où elle a opéré pendant plus de 25 ans. C’est en l’an 2000 qu’elle a décidé de construire une nouvelle usine et de s’installer à Sherbrooke,  dans de nouveaux locaux répondant aux exigences et aux normes régissant le domaine de l’alimentation. En 1996, elle a été intégrée à un large groupe nord-américain d’entreprises manufacturières produisant des emballages flexibles variés.

Spécialisé dans la fabrication de fenêtres coulissantes pour coulage en place, FORMTECH détient le titre de concepteur innovateur de cette méthode d’installation.  Ce concept facilite et diminue le temps de main-d’œuvre des coffreurs et entrepreneurs. Jusqu’à ce jour, l’organisation offre la fenêtre la plus performante et facile d’installation de ce marché.

Technoclip

La gamme de produits TECHNOCLIP est la plus performante de sa classe sur le marché. Ses performances énergétiques et physiques sont incomparables. De plus, il n’y a que 2 pièces à assembler, elle est certainement la plus facile et rapide à installer !

 

Disponible en PVC NOIR

Saviez-vous que nos fenêtres de couleurs noires ne sont pas peintes? Elles sont faites à partir d’un procédé de « capstock » ici même en usine. Le capstock nous permet d’ajouter une couche de poudre noire de quelques millièmes en surface des différentes pièces fabriquées.  Il s’applique directement dans l’extrusion pour laisser un fini de couleur beaucoup plus robuste et durable que la peinture à prix compétitif.

Aucun
risque de bris

What is RAS Aquaculture?

Recirculating Aquaculture System, or RAS, is a technique for raising aquatic species in a closed, indoor, land-based system.

Benefits of using Recirculating Aquaculture Systems:

Minimizes Water Consumption
Provides Maximum Control of the Environment,
Reduces exposure to parasites, disease, and predators.

OUR STORY



Acriart was founded in 1981 by passionate entrepreneurs who shared a vision of craftsmanship and dedication to creating high-quality products. 

Over the years, the company grew, earning a reputation for its precision and personalized service in the creation of commemorative items. As the business evolved, the founders passed the torch to a new generation of leadership, who share the same passion and commitment to excellence. 

Today, under new management, we honor our founders' legacy by embracing innovation and new technology, while maintaining the attention to detail that defines our brand. Our mission is to guide clients with expert advice and exceptional craftsmanship, ensuring their satisfaction every step of the way.

OUR VALUES

 

At Acriart, our values are at the heart of everything we do. We pride ourselves on being meticulous in every detail, ensuring that each project reflects the highest standards of craftsmanship. Creativity drives our approach, allowing us to deliver innovative solutions that meet the unique needs of our clients. We’re highly adaptive, able to adjust quickly to changes and work under tight deadlines, always keeping our clients' goals at the forefront. Listening to our clients is essential to us, and we strive to build strong, human connections with them to create a collaborative experience from start to finish.



WE ARE PROUD TO BE HIGHLY RATED BY DISTRIBUTORS.
OUR TEAM



Our team at Acriart is built on longevity and experience, with many members having been with us for years, contributing to our strong foundation. We are organized into specialized departments: Office, Creative, Production and Expedition, each playing a vital role in delivering top-quality results. Our collaborative approach ensures that every team member is aligned and communicates seamlessly, allowing us to handle every project efficiently and with precision from start to finish. Working with Acriart means working with passionate professionals who are dedicated to bringing your vision to life with care, creativity, and commitment.

Welcome to Unique Blowmoulding Inc.

Unique Blowmoulding Inc. is your one-stop shop for custom design and production of plastic bottles and jars. With over 40 years of experience in the plastic industry and over 10 years of innovating the customized bottle manufacturing process, we are confident in our capabilities to produce a product that will meet your needs.

Our custom moulds are built in-house to expedite our processing and provide products that are tailored to your exact specifications. If you cannot find what you are looking for, feel free to contact us and we will be pleased to work with you on a design and build tooling to create your perfect package. We have served a number of industries throughout North America, including personal care, nutraceuticals, food, automotive, household, lawn and garden and private label packaging. We can guarantee high quality service and products, competitive pricing and a short turnaround time!

Learn More

We provide fully customized solutions for manufacturing plastic bottles and jars. Every aspect of the manufacturing process is performed in-house, from consultation to design and engineering to final production.

Petrolia Plastics Inc. is a custom mold maker and plastic injection molder that has supplied highly specialized and technologically sophisticated plastic components to the telecom, electronics and other industry sectors since 1984.  Petrolia's customer base includes numerous high-tech, electronics and OEM’s in Canada and the U.S. including customers in the automotive and medical sectors.  Product is currently shipped to customers throughout Canada, the U.S., Mexico and Europe.




Petrolia Plastics Inc. developed an international reputation for its adoption of competitive and innovative technologies and is one of only a handful of companies in North America to have successfully mastered the InMold decorating (lMD) process. Petrolia specializes in the InMold decorating (IMD) process where a decorative film is applied to a plastic part during the molding process resulting in a level of quality and consistency unmatched by any other process.  Fully integrated CAD/CAM and production systems are used throughout the manufacturing process from product development, through mold manufacturing to production and inspection of parts.   In-house, custom-designed, integrated inspection systems help to ensure exacting product standards.




Petrolia was the second plastics company in North America to register an ISO quality system (9002 in 1992).  In 2003 Petrolia become accredited with the ISO 9001:2000 certification.  Petrolia is also QS9000 compliant to meet the quality requirements of our customers in the automotive industry.

30 Years’ Experience Manufacturing Biaxially & Mono Oriented Film

EVLON® Compostable Film, research and development trials for pre-commercialization purposes and production of APTRA breathable film are our core business.

News
What We Do...
EVLON® Compostable Film... Are you ready to go green?

Environmentally friendly, compostable clear film and sheet material, EVLON®, is made from NatureWorks PLA Ingeo resin or Total Corbion resin.

Made from plants, EVLON®, fills the worldwide desire to utilize renewable resources and provides an environmentally friendly, crystal clear, strong product that can be used in a variety of packaging applications such as sealed produce bags, confectionary bags, bakery bags and sealed over-wrap.

The film can be plain or printed and laminated, for horizontal and vertical packaging machines.

EVLON® products can be industrially composted, and the material will breakdown and revert to carbon dioxide and water in less than 90 days.

Food contact certification in USA, EU and Canada.

R&D
Research & Development Pre-Production Trial Runs

We offer a product development facility for customers to develop biaxially and mono direction oriented products. Products can move from the lab environment and into a pre-production phase for assessment and modifications to achieve the desired physical properties. 

Capabilities are a biaxial orientation line and a mono direction line, capable of laminating additional layers on to sheet as well as extruding and orienting sheet and film in large quantities. 

 

The facility has been used by several of the world's largest petrochemical, packaging and food companies.

Aptra®
APTRA® Breathable Film

BI-AX manufactures Aptra® Classic and Aptra® UV films.

Aptra® is a breathable film used as a composite with other materials. Though it barely registers on the scales, this unique film provides an exceptional combination of barrier properties and breathability.

Aptra® is easily laminated with a wide variety of substrates using several methods. Composite structures utilizing spunbond nonwovens are one of the many configurations possible. Lamination can be accomplished by point bonding with heated calenders, sonic bonding, heat sealing and spray adhesives.

A wide variety of applications: roofing underlayment, housing wrap, disposable protective garments, medical apparel and industrial garments.

Making evlon compostable film since 2001...doing our part for the environment
History
30+ Years Manufacturing Biaxially and Mono Oriented Film

BI-AX International Inc. was founded by brothers David and Tom Inglis in 1986 and production of biaxially oriented polypropylene (BOPP) began in 1987. Initial markets were pressure sensitive tape and food packaging.

In 2000, the operation expanded with a 220,000 square foot plant in Wingham, Ontario, Canada.
Since then niche markets in product development trials, compostable film ( EVLON® ) and breathable, microporous products (Aptra® ) have dominated our business.

Another capability is mono-directional orientation of heavy sheet with the ability to add extra layers. This can be done with sheet that has been made in other locations with various layer configurations.

Recently we added the availability of GMO-free PLA resin for our EVLON line of products.

Much of our time is used in toll manufacturing for other companies that require production of their specialty products. This is a more economical way for them to enter a growing market than the purchase of expensive equipment.

recycling together for our future

	

Who We Are

Merlin Plastics is a recycler and processor of post-consumer and post-industrial plastic container packaging. 

Merlin Plastics located in Delta, BC, Canada, is the headquarters for the Merlin Group of Companies.  Merlin Plastics has two facilities in BC:  Merlin Plastics – Gifford and Merlin Plastics – Delta. Merlin Plastics – Gifford is the state-of-the-art container sortation plant, one of the largest on the West Coast, where the materials from the curbside blue bins collected in BC get sorted into their respective streams.  Merlin Plastics – Delta is the processing plant that processes the various plastic container packaging into recycled flake and pellet. We also have a facility in Calgary, AB that recycles and processes PET plastics into recycled flake and pellet.

Our high value, quality recycled plastic products are being integrated into various commercial and industrial industries as an alternative to virgin resin for manufacturers to produce similar or alternative consumer goods.

“From Curbside to Pellet and Flake”

Our Mission

We are dedicated and committed to providing environmental services by recycling discarded packaging in an environmentally sound, economically efficient and socially responsible fashion.

Merlin Plastics continuously work with brand owners, retailers, and industry associations to improve packaging design for recyclability as well as develop alternatives for ongoing sustainable solutions. In lieu of ‘cradle-to-grave’ end-of-life cycle for plastic products, our objective is for a seamless, continuous Circular Economy.
