QUE FAIT ROTOPLAST?
 

ROTOPLAST œuvre dans le domaine du plastique et utilise le procédé de moulage par rotation (rotomoulage) depuis sa création. Nous sommes le leader en développement, fabrication et assemblage de pièces de plastique rotomoulées en sous-traitance pour tous les secteurs d’activités. Notre système de gestion de la production, du contrôle de la qualité et de l’amélioration continue permet de nous démarquer et d’assurer une progression constante de nos activités. Nous desservons un nombre croissant de grands donneurs d’ordres, de multinationales ou de PME.

​QU'EST-CE QUE LE ROTOMOULAGE ?

Le rotomoulage est une méthode de production de pièces en plastique qui offre de nombreux avantages par rapport à d'autres procédés de moulage de plastique tels que le moulage par soufflage, le formage sous vide ou le moulage par injection. Bien que le rotomoulage ne soit pas aussi rapide que le soufflage pour la production de grandes quantités de pièces, il présente moins de limitations en termes de conception et de géométrie des pièces produites. En effet, le rotomoulage est le seul procédé qui permette de produire des pièces plus grandes, aux formes plus complexes et aux parois plus épaisses, ce qui n'est possible avec aucun autre procédé de moulage des matières plastiques. En outre, les moules (outillages) utilisés pour le rotomoulage sont beaucoup moins coûteux que ceux utilisés pour le soufflage ou l'injection (les moules coûtent environ 10 fois moins cher, ce qui réduit considérablement les coûts de production). En résumé, le rotomoulage est une solution de production efficace et économique pour les pièces plastiques de grande taille et de forme complexe.

 

Nos clients sont des visionnaires qui recherchent un collaborateur fiable capable de transformer leurs concepts en réalité. Nous possédons l'expertise nécessaire en matière d'ingénierie, de production et de logistique pour atteindre cet objectif. Ils apprécient nos produits de haute qualité et notre rapidité d'exécution. Contactez-nous dès aujourd'hui pour obtenir un devis et commencer à travailler avec nous.

QUELQUES AVANTAGES DE ROTOPLAST

Vos questions, nos réponses

LE PROCÉDÉ

Une poudre de plastique est chargée dans un moule qui est introduit dans un four à haute température et tourné sur deux axes. La poudre fond, formant une couche de plastique dans la surface intérieure du moule. Ensuite, le moule est refroidi pour permettre au plastique de se solidifier. Finalement, le moule est ouvert afin de libérer la pièce parfaitement formée qui vient d’être produite.

Lors de la fabrication de la pièce, une multitude d’éléments peuvent être inclus tels que : des insertions métalliques, des filets, des ouvertures, des décalques, etc.

De plus, presque tous les finis de surfaces peuvent être créés à l’aide de diverses textures et/ou de peinture. Le procédé permet également de produire des formes complexes dans une variété de matériel, tout en contrôlant l’épaisseur des parois.

LES AVANTAGES

Coût de l’outillage très bas en comparaison avec l’injection ou le « blow molding »

Faible coût des pièces

Permet la production de petites ou de grandes quantités

Possibilité infinie de finis de surface avec texture et ajout de logo en 3D

Choix de couleurs illimité

Contrôle des épaisseurs des parois;

Approuvé FDA et NSF61;

Grande flexibilité dans la production : insertions métalliques, filets, ouvertures, etc.;

Pièces simples ou complexes, de petits ou de très grands formats;

Pas de soudure ni de joints.

Certifiée ISO 9001, notre équipe est fière de pouvoir vous garantir des produits et un service qui répondent aux plus hautes normes de qualité.

Welcome to PCI.

PCI Pushes 
the Boundaries

in the fabrication of innovative composite products for clients who are at the cutting edge of the aerospace, defence, medical and marine industries.

Let's Get Started
In 2014 PCI 
Was Created 

to fill the need for innovative minds to collaborate in the creation of revolutionary products in the composite manufacturing industry.

Work With Us
PCI’s 29,000 Square Foot 
Composite Manufacturing Facility.

In 2018, PCI moved to a new 29,000 ft2 facility at 20 Fasken Drive in Toronto, next to Toronto Pearson International Airport. Our recent expansion has positioned PCI to take on bigger projects with greater scale. In addition to the larger footprint, other improvements include a 3,000 ft2 clean room, inventory control zones, a walk-in freezer and a 5-ton overhead crane.

A Full In-House 
Suite of Proprietary Equipment

allowing increased efficiencies and decreased lead times for all of our clients’ custom composite fabrication needs.

Let's Build It
Established: 2014

100% Canadian Owned 
Performance

From ultra-light racing catamarans to UAVs and super cars, PCI has a more than a decade of experience developing, testing and producing high performance and high-quality components to fully finished, assembled products ready for their specific application.

Customer

We methodically scope and execute our projects with quality and consistency. Our Quality Management System is certified to AS 9100 Rev D and ISO 9001:2015 standards. Our facility and processes are aligned so projects exceed customer expectations.

Innovation

A core competency of PCI, innovative minds work to iterate prototype solutions and processes for any project. From tooling to production methods and custom-built machines, at PCI we continually research and develop to expand our capabilities.

WELCOME

Dramatic changes are taking place in the recycling industry around the world and right here at home.  Every step of the way Billy Boot has kept up with these changes.    In fact it was very easy for Billy Boot to follow the rapidly changing plastic industry.  Afterall Billy Boot is made from recycled plastics from the very beginning.  Joining the recycling movement is not difficult, but it does require a few basic changes in the way people deal with household garbage. First, it helps to think about ways that materials may be reused or recycled. Then, it's easy for family members to train themselves to separate recyclables from the household waste stream.  We invite everyone to take a fresh look at our new product lineup.  See for yourself how Billy Boot has  new products perfectly suited to recycling.

RECYCLING IDEAS

Today, many products are made from recycled materials. For example, plastics are used to produce appliance handles and insulation, aluminum cans are made into rain gutters and window frames, and newspapers become cereal boxes and roofing material. The list of products made from recycled materials grows every day, as does the list of recyclable materials for which there is a market. Joining the recycling movement is not difficult, but it does require a few basic changes in the way people deal with household garbage. First, it helps to think about ways that materials may be reused or recycled. Then, it's easy for family members to train themselves to separate recyclables from the household waste stream. (Many of us have found that school-age children make willing and effective Family Recycling Officers.)

If your community has curbside recycling, the rest is easy. If it doesn't, then all it takes is a periodic trip to the growing number of recycling drop-off points, many of which may be listed in your local newspaper.

Recycling reduces the amount of garbage going into landfills. And, just as important, recycling also conserves energy because in most cases less energy is needed to make products out of recyclable materials than from raw materials.

Des produits conçus pour les amateurs de chasse
Beaucoup de propriétaires de véhicules motorisés récréatifs sont également des amateurs de chasse. Ces derniers savent mieux que quiconque que lors d’une expédition, il est toujours utile de pouvoir profiter d’espace de rangement supplémentaire. C’est pourquoi tant de chasseurs font confiance aux produits Wes Industries. Ceux-ci apprécient également la construction robuste de nos coffres et accessoires. Même hors des sentiers battus, ceux-ci restent solidement en place et gardent leur contenu bien à l’abri des intempéries.
Wes Industries : un réseau de détaillants implanté à la grandeur Québec
Peu importe où vous vous trouvez dans la province, sachez qu’il y a un détaillant à proximité, prêt à vous faire apprécier la qualité de fabrication de nos coffres et accessoires pour véhicules tout-terrain, UTV et motoneiges. Wes Industries, des produits fabriqués ici, pour répondre aux besoins des gens d’ici
Tous nos coffres et accessoires sont fabriqués ici même au Québec, dans notre usine de Princeville. Nous sommes fiers de pouvoir mettre à contribution le savoir-faire des gens d’ici, afin de développer des produits qui sont adaptés aux réalités de notre environnement et des besoins des propriétaires de véhicules récréatifs motorisés.

Welcome to Granby Composites where innovation meets reliability.

At Granby Composites, excellence is not just a goal – it’s an expectation. Count on us for unparalleled engineering services, functionality, and durability for all your fiberglass water tank storage needs, whether it’s for commercial water storage, rainwater harvesting, fire protection, municipal water management, or more!

From the definition of technical specifications to after-sales service, including assistance in the production of quotes, our qualified engineering team supports and advises you to maximize the positive benefits associated with your aboveground and underground fiberglass tanks.

Easy to reach by phone and email, our team members are passionate about their work, where each project represents a challenge of personalization.

At Granby Composites, each of your needs is considered to provide you with a customized and ready-to-install solution. Do you want a manhole at the place x rather than y? Of course! Do you need a valve in this place? No problem! Do you need an insulated tank instead? It’s like it’s done.

 

YOUR WATER TANK MANUFACTURER ALLY, FROM SPECIFICATION TO IMPLEMENTATION

The main benefits of working with our team:

Competence – Our team captures your needs and translates them into drawings to illustrate them; your team can then develop the mechanical and technical drawings required for approval.

Customization – Together with your engineers, our team designs the tank or pumping station that meets the exact specifications of your liquid recovery, storage, or management project.

Ready to install – Plus, throughout the process, our team ensures that these products are easily integrated into your on-site facilities and equipment for you to use as soon as they are received.

QUADRA PLAST has been a leader in the extrusion of polymer profiles since 1991. With an experienced team, the company stands out by being much more than a simple supplier of extruded products: it positions itself as an integrated partner in its customers' supply chain. Service and innovation are at the heart of its activity. QUADRA PLAST is committed to offering tailor-made solutions meeting the specific needs of each client, thus guaranteeing optimal satisfaction and increased efficiency in their production processes.

The company continually invests in research and development in order to offer high-quality, cutting-edge products. Thanks to its innovation-driven approach, QUADRA PLAST is able to meet the most stringent market requirements and anticipate emerging trends. This allows its customers to benefit from innovative and competitive solutions, ensuring their long-term success.

Customer service at QUADRA PLAST is not limited to providing top quality products; it also includes comprehensive technical support, new product development assistance, and efficient logistics. This global approach makes QUADRA PLAST a reliable and indispensable partner for its customers.

For over three decades, QUADRA PLAST has built a reputation for excellence and reliability in the polymer profile extrusion sector, and continues to evolve to stay at the forefront of the industry, always putting service and innovation at the center of its concerns.

Pour vos projets de rénovation et de construction,

 

faites affaire avec les experts de chez Portes et fenêtres Varin. Avec 80 ans d’expérience, de qualité et de service, nous sommes les experts des portes et fenêtres. Chez nous, vous serez accueillis par un personnel compétent et chaleureux, que vous soyez un particulier ou un entrepreneur.

Vous prévoyez rénover, construire, ou simplement changer une porte ou une fenêtre ? Portes d’acier, portes patio, portes de garage, fenêtres hybrides : nous offrons la plus vaste sélection de portes et fenêtres de la région. De plus, vous trouverez tout sous le même toit et n’aurez aucunement besoin de faire affaire avec un intermédiaire. We produce industrial, specialty, and transportation tanks as well as material handling containers of various capacities. We have over 45 years of experience. Our tanks meet the ASTM-D-1998 standards and we are ISO 9001:2015 certified.

Vertical Storage Tanks
At ACO, we are committed to providing sauperior vertical storage tanks that cater to many industries across Canada and the USA. Our design expertise extends to creating seamless, one-piece, closed-top storage tanks that are specifically constructed to house corrosive chemicals and other substances that may pose potential health risks.
Secondary Containment Basins
Avoid accidental spills and their environmental impact! Made of polyethylene, our secondary containment tanks make it easier for you to comply with regulations on the containment of spills of hazardous products and waste. They are resistant to UV light, chemicals, corrosion and low temperature impact. Like our tanks, they are constructed in one piece, so there are no seams or welds.
Open Top Storage Tanks
If you need access to the inside of your tanks, open vertical tanks are the way to go. Like the closed tanks, they are molded from a single piece of polyethylene plastic that is resistant to corrosion, chemicals, low-temperature impact and UV light. NSF 61 listed and FDA compliant for potable water applications.. These tanks can be used for mixing and blending different liquids and pastes: mixer stands, hinged lids and other accessories can be sold as options.
IBC accessories
Discover our accessories specially designed for IBCs. Each part is designed to maximize the functionality of your containers.
Poly Tanks, IBC Totes, Containers & Pallets manufacturer
ACO Container Systems – A Division of Rotoplast Inc.

ACO Containers is a Canadian manufacturer of globally recognized high-quality rotationally-molded tanks and products.

A division of Rotoplast Inc., ACO is a world-renowned North American manufacturers of high quality, polyethylene, rotationally-molded plastic and HDPE storage tanks.

Based in Toronto, Ontario, ACO produces a wide variety of plastic storage tanks, closed top tanks, containment basins, open top and double wall storage, chemical and industrial tanks, pallet tanks, transportation tanks, horizontal tanks, flat-bottomed round tanks and other specialty polyethylene products.

ACO storage tanks are used by various sectors such as the chemical processing industry, municipal water treatment plants, pulp and paper sector, and many other industrial groups across Canada and the USA.

In addition to the unsurpassed quality of our tanks, basins and related products, ACO Containers is also known for its ingenuity. You will be amazed at our great flexibility.

Our experienced sales team are quick to respond to your project and will design a tank to suit your needs in a timely manner. If you have an outdated tank that needs to be replaced quickly, we will also be happy to assist you.

Finally, you will undoubtedly appreciate our human-scale customer service provided by our available and attentive team. In a warm, reassuring and professional manner, we will rigorously follow up your small or large project with transparency and accountability.

PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT

1/5

​Why Rotomolding? 

Rotational molded products are cost effective alternatives to traditional fiberglass and metal options.  Compared to other plastic processes, rotomolding tooling costs are significantly lower and minimum quantites are much smaller, both of which reduce the financial risks of new product development.

More Info

Services

We offer a full line of services to support your product development needs.  From napkin sketch to finished product we can help take your concept to market reality by providing product and tooling design, contract manufacturing and custom material processing to ensure that your product is made to the highest quality standards.

More Info

Product Development

We have developed products in a variety of industries from Medical to Mining.  Our years of experience coupled with our broad range of industry involvement allows us to bring these collective learnings and expertise to your project needs.  Let us help you get the most out of your product designs.

Bienvenue sur notre site internet
 
 
A PROPOS DE NOUS 
 
 
Notre entreprise QVP inc. fondée en 1996, est spécialisée dans le moulage de pièces de plastique par injection. Avec plus de 20 ans d'expérience en développement de produits, nous avons les connaissances et l'expertise nécessaires pour développer des pièces de plastique et assemblage très complexe.
 
Nous avons la capacité de concevoir et d'élaborer des prototypes, de gérer les outillages prototypes, de productions et les outillages secondaires, de produire selon les relâches de commandes correspondant aux besoins du client et d'assurer un suivi de production et de contrôle de la qualité de première classe.
 
Nos clients proviennent de différents secteurs d'activités très variés tels que : l'industriel, le récréatif,  le promotionnel,  l'électronique, l'optique, le sanitaire, le jouet, etc.. 
 
Nos connaissances en moulage par injection jumelées à notre logiciel 3D-CAD nous permettent de bien analyser et de bien concevoir les pièces et d'interagir avec nos clients et fournisseurs avec professionnalisme. 
 
Notre expérience et notre collaboration avec notre réseau de fournisseurs et sous-traitants sont des éléments-clés dans le développement de produits.
 
Avec nous, vous verrez que nous gérons vos projets d'une façon simple malgré la complexité des produits à développer. Vous obtiendrez vos pièces livrées clé en main selon vos spécifications. 
 
 
ÉQUIPEMENTS DE PRODUCTION
Presses à injections : 80 à 385 tonnes
Soudeuse ultrasonique
Impression à chaud
 
 
LOCALISATION  
Situé tout près de l'autoroute 20, sortie #414 à Saint-Jean-Port-Joli, à seulement une heure de Québec.
 
 
Merci à tous nos clients et fournisseurs pour leur support continuel et de nous faire confiance depuis toutes ces années.
 
 

 

Welcome to our website
 
 
ABOUT US 
 
Founded in 1996, QVP inc. specializes in injection molding plastic parts. With more than twenty years of experience in product development, we have the know-how and expertise to design and develop complex injection molding parts and plastic assemblies.
 
We design custom tooling and manufacturing prototypes, manage manufacture and quality control processes as well as track contract release order according to customers specific needs.
 
We cater for the industrial, recreational, promotional, electronic, optical, sanitary, toys markets as well as many more specialty market segments.
 
Our injection molding knowledge combined with our 3D-CAD software allow us to analyse and design parts and assemblies effectively and interface professionally with our clients and suppliers.
 
Our synergistic approach to design and collaboration between clients, suppliers and sub-contractors is key in our product development process.
 
Together we manage projets effectively and overcome complex product developments. We provide manufacturing and custom turnkey solutions according to our clients exacting specifications.
 
 
MANUFACTURING EQUIPMENTS
Injection molding machine : 80 to 385 tons
Ultrasonic welding
Hot Stamping
 
 
WHERE WE ARE
Located in Saint-Jean-Port-Joli, exit 414, highway 20, only one-hour drive from Quebec city. 
 
 
We would like to thanks our clients and suppliers for their continuing loyalty and trust years after years.

开云手机官方网站(中国)有限公司-官网首页（简称：春洋重工），坐落于依山傍海、交通便利的大连甘井子区革镇堡羊圈工业园。 开云手机官方网站(中国)有限公司-官网首页专业生产下顶拉式卷板机、10MN-165MN快锻油压机及大型液压站、减速机、液压缸、大型液压卷板机专用调心轴承、翻盘机、焊接滚轮架等，具有较轻的设计和生产能力，另拥有冶炼、发电等大型钢结构普通焊接、特焊、机械加工、装配的生产能力。 2012年根据市场需求，推出了金属厚壁小直径筒体冷压成型技术，成为一项特色产品，目前为国内多家企业外协，取得了良好的经济效益和社会效益。 2013年建立了大连春洋贸易有限公司，隶属于大连春洋重工机械制作有限公司，具有独立的进出口权，主要从事对日本，欧美等国有关机械加工方面的进出口贸易。2014年建立了大连荷花湾家庭农场。大连春洋重工机械制作有限公司现有员工200余人，其中各类专业技术人员40余人，公司占地面积近7万平方米，其中建筑面积近4万平方米，拥有8个车间、3个露天吊装场地。 春洋重工奉行“创建一流企业、造就一流人才、做出一流贡献”的企业理念，“安全，节能，高效，优质”的服务宗旨，依托良好的外部环境和政策支持，快速发展，真诚为国内外商客进行更广泛的合作与交谈。

About

Flexcim Manufacturing Services Inc. is a diverse Canadian manufacturing company located in Edmonton, Canada. Our mission is to reverse the trend towards offshoring and repatriate production into Canada.

All of our products are proudly made in Canada. We work within the community and source the majority of our supplies and materials locally. As a result, we have a good relationship with many local businesses. Our relationships with customers are vertically integrated into our manufacturing process. Orders are immediately shipped from stock and replenished based on the “Supermarket” model in lean manufacturing.

QUALITY PLASTIC PACKAGING
OUR PROCESS

Century Packaging Ltd. has been providing customers with quality plastic packaging since 1994. We take great pride in producing quality bottles in PET and HDPE in a range of sizes from 1oz to 4 ltr.



All our production methods use state-of-the-art extrusion blow molding and reheat stretch blow molding machines made in either the U.S. or Canada.



The bottles, jars and containers we create are used all over the North America for numerous products and industries including: Food, Beverage, Pharmaceutical, Cosmetics, Petroleum, Domestic Cleaners and Personal Care.



With over 100 clients in the household and commercial sectors, our work can be found in stores all over North America.



CONSULTATION

The first part of our process is to work with our customers to understand their packaging needs.

A production consultant will discuss with you to determine if an existing mould can be used or if a custom design is needed. Clients will then be presented with multiple options to choose from which will include size of mold and type of plastic and colour, if needed.



Once specifications for the project have been determined, and a mold made or provided, technicians use this information to create samples for client approval. After approval and sign-off, the production process can begin.



SETUP

Century Packaging Ltd. uses state-of-the-art extrusion blow molding and reheat stretch blow molding machines. Our experienced technicians set up each machine according to our customer's specifications. This set up includes installing the specified mold, plastic and colour.



PRODUCTION

Extrusion Blow Molding

Our plastic products come to us in the form of tiny pellets. These pellets are fed into the blow molding machines using a sophisticated vacuum system.



In an extruder, heat is introduced and the pellets are melted and mixed with a desired color if needed. Once blended, the machines extrudes the plastic in to a suitable sized parison required for the mold to capture and continue the blow moulding process.



Next, the mold closes on the parison and uses air pressure to blow it into the shape of the mold  and holds the plastic against the water cooled mold cavity to solidify and cool the plastic to the final shape.  Once complete, the machine releases the newly formed bottle onto a conveyor destined for the finishing area.



Reheat Stretch Blow Molding

Reheat stretch blow molding starts with what is called a "preform" with a specific weight and neck finish.



Once a preform and mold are selected and installed in the machine the preform is loaded in the machine and transported to a infrared oven, which heats the preform to the desired temperature. Then the preform is transported to the mold where the mold closes on the perform and a stretch rod stretches the perform. At the same time, high pressure air is introduced to stretch the preform to the shape of the mold and holds the plastic against the water cooled mold cavity to solidify and cool the plastic to the final shape. 



Once complete, the machine releases the newly formed bottle onto a conveyor destined for packing.



FINISHING & QUALITY CONTROL

This step is the most important to us. Even after a perfect molding process some bottles can have extra plastic or imperfections. The finishing area is where each bottle is examined by hand and trimmed of excess plastic if needed.



All of Century Packaging�s technicians are educated and trained to carefully inspect for any flaws that may occur during production as well as insuring machinery is always running at optimum performance levels.



Click here to view a video of a blow mould machine in action



Environmental note: All excess plastics left after production is ground up and recycled to be used again. Century Packaging Ltd does not use any plastic containing BPA (Bisphenol A).

BENEFITS OF CHOOSING CUSTOM WINDOWS AND DOORS IN WINNIPEG

Custom windows and doors on your building can help it stand out and create a more welcoming and high-end look. Spending a little more money on customized woodwork offers a range of benefits that outweigh the price. Some reasons to choose custom windows and doors for your building are:
 

Add value
Custom windows and door installations can increase your home’s valuation. Our experts can help add beauty to your home inside and out. We will work with you to create a custom design that is perfect for your style and space. It can enhance both the interior and exterior of your home or commercial building. If you plan to sell your property later, upgrading your windows and doors will ensure a better price.
 

Better functionality and design options
PVC custom windows provide no maintenance and give energy efficiency warmth in winter and fresh air in summer. Custom windows and doors can also improve the functionality and practicality of your property. You can use special glass or hardware for added security or more robust frames for better sound isolation and protection against extreme weather conditions. Our superior-quality installations make your space more user-friendly. When it comes to customization, the sky is the limit. You have to give us your idea, and we will use the best materials to make your design idea possible.
 

Cost-effective
Although custom doors and windows are an expensive one-time investment, they will help you gain more control over future repair and replacement costs. PVC is more durable, requires less maintenance over time, and improves energy efficiency, which leads to low energy bills, heating requirements, and more savings.
 

Easy installation
Fitting ready-made stock windows and doors can be complicated. The window size may not match your home's openings, and you may need to chisel out your wall or add some moulding to make it fit. Fortunately, we make custom-sized windows for homeowners who want to do their installation. Our custom-made windows require less prep work and fewer additional materials to complete the installation.

MAINTAINING YOUR CUSTOM WINDOWS AND DOORS: EASY TIPS FOR LONGEVITY

Investing in custom windows and doors in Winnipeg is a big decision. Choosing windows and doors from Duraseal Windows & Doors Co and keeping them in good shape ensures they add value to your home for years. Here's how to maintain their beauty and function:
 

Regular cleaning: Clean the glass and frames with a non-abrasive cleaner. Avoid harsh chemicals that could damage the finish. Use a damp cloth to wipe down doors and remove dust. Quickly fix any chips or scratches for painted doors to prevent further damage.
 

Check for damage: Ensure your windows and doors are regularly free of rust, chips, and cracks. Early resolution of these concerns can help avert more serious ones.
 

Maintain weatherstripping and seals: Ensure that weatherstripping and seals are intact and in good condition. Replace damaged seals to prevent drafts and preserve energy efficiency.
 

Lube moving parts: Lube hinges, locks, and handles regularly to keep them functioning smoothly. Use a lubricant with a silicone base to prevent dust from drawing in.
 

Examine and clean the drains: To avoid water damage, ensure the window and door drains are debris-free and operate correctly.
 

Professional Inspections: Schedule regular check-ups with professionals from Duraseal Windows & Doors Co to keep your windows and doors in top condition. Our experts offer advice and services to maintain your investment.
 

Following these simple maintenance steps will help extend the life of your custom windows and doors and ensure you continue enjoying their benefits. If you want to learn more about maintaining your windows and doors, speak to us today.

The world's largest manufacturer of plastic spiral binding products & equipment
24 Hours A Day – In 24 Different Countries Around The World

Our company is Gateway Bookbinding Systems Ltd. Our product is PLASTIKOIL® - The most attractive and functional mechanical binding system on the market. Made from the highest grade compounds, PLASTIKOIL® plastic spiral binding sets the industry's standards. Strong and durable - yet flexible and lightweight – PLASTIKOIL® is CPSIA compliant (Lead free and phthalate free). PLASTIKOIL® bound books lay flat when opened - with the ability to fold back a full 360 degrees. Pages will never pull apart and the coil will not bend or distort during shipping. PLASTIKOIL® is available in 45 different colors - in coil diameters from 6 mm (1/4") to 50 mm (2"). Custom colors; custom lengths; all pitch options.

Gateway Bookbinding systems specializes in plastic spiral binding. It's what we do - it's all that we do - 24 hours a day. We understand the product and we understand the process - better than anyone. We have been manufacturing plastic spiral binding products and equipment for over 50 years. PLASTIKOIL® is currently being manufactured in 24 different countries around the globe. As the world's most extensive coil manufacturer, our objective always has been and continues to be that of dedicated customer assistance and support - working with our customers to provide them with the most feasible, most economical solutions for all of their plastic spiral binding needs.

Gateway Bookbinding Systems Ltd. – The Plastic Spiral Experts.

Experts en Ventilation Souterraine pour Mines

Depuis 1999, Mécanicad se positionne comme un leader dans la ventilation des mines souterraines. Grâce à une approche innovante et des technologies de pointe, notre équipe a transformé les standards de sécurité et d’efficacité dans ce secteur. Nous nous engageons à améliorer les conditions de travail des mineurs tout en optimisant les performances.

DÉCOUVREZ NOS EXPERTS
Système de Ventilation Efficace pour Mines et Tunnels

Mécanicad propose un système de ventilation à haute efficacité, conçu pour optimiser les projets miniers et tunneliers. Ce système innovant permet non seulement d’améliorer la circulation de l’air et la sécurité des travailleurs, mais aussi de réduire la consommation d’énergie, contribuant ainsi à des opérations plus durables et rentables.

DÉCOUVREZ NOS RÉALISATIONS
Conduits en Plastique de Haute Performance

Nos conduits en plastique se distinguent par le facteur de friction le plus bas de l’industrie, ce qui les rend particulièrement efficaces. Faciles à installer, ces conduits sont également réutilisables, durables et légers. Ils garantissent des performances optimales, offrant une solution fiable pour vos besoins en ventilation.

Specialty & Wire Cable Inc.

For over 25 years, Specialty Wire & Cable Inc. has been delivering cabling solutions for businesses all over North America. We are dedicated to manufacturing the highest quality cables and connectors that your business and communities can depend on. Our team of dedicated engineers and technicians use innovative technologies and superior materials to build and assemble our cables. Expect every SWC product to be rigorously tested for perfect performance and quick delivery.

Oil & Gas

Our ruggedized cables are used in oil and gas exploration, including: land and marine drilling, refineries, pipe inspection, stimulation, seismic and more.

Marine

SWC uses superior techniques and materials to manufacture reliable underwater cable assemblies for shallow depth applications.

Agriculture

SWC utilizes food safe plastics & materials to protect the cable, ensuring reliability for irrigation, crop production and grain elevators.

Geotechnical

Our experience in wind, solar, hydro, bridging and dams is made possible because of our extensive customization ability in both cable manufacturing and assembly. This includes capability to encapsulate/mold PCB’s and thermistors. We can also provide thermocouple strings for multiple applications.

Custom Solutions

If you are looking for a unique cable solution and have encountered high up-front costs or lengthy lead times, call SWC. We will design, manufacture, assemble and ship your specialty cable solution faster than any competitor. Alternatively, we can modify pre-assembled cables to fit your project or industry challenges. Private label cable products with custom printing options are also available using your businesses logo, name, part number, or product details.

Our Process
Advanced Manufacturing
We offer a diverse portfolio of insulating, braiding, jacketing and overmolding materials, customized to best fit your project needs. To minimize design and testing costs, our professionals will work with you to create a prototype for field operations. Trust that SWC will engineer a solution that works for your process and business application.
Specialty Materials
The difference between a standard cable versus a SWC cable is the superior quality in materials used during the manufacturing and assembly processes, using ruggedization standards for the harshest environments.

About SPI Plastics

Established in 1972, SPI Plastics Inc. has since maintained our mission of providing world-class products and services while leading the way in technology-based rotational molding techniques. Today, our products are represented in over 40 countries worldwide, ranging from livestock waterers to commercial playground equipment and indoor play systems.

Our primary focus is on meeting the needs of our customers. To achieve this, we are constantly adapting and embracing new technologies. We understand that the utilization of cutting-edge technology is key to fulfilling the high standards and expectations of our global customer base.

We also prioritize the growth of our employees, recognizing that their personal dedication and innovation are essential to our success. We continuously challenge our team members to develop their knowledge and capabilities to become the best that they can be. As a company, we firmly believe that knowledge combined with dedication and innovation is our greatest strength.

Why Do Home Owners Choose Fibertec For Energy Efficient Fiberglass Windows and Doors?

Fiberglass Windows and Doors Manufactured with Triple Glazed Glass that are recognized as a World Leader for Energy Efficiency in the window and door industry.

We provide one of the most comprehensive lines of high performance energy-efficient windows and doors made with Fiberglass frames in North America, which will definitely save you money on energy!

Fibertec provides uncompromising quality in their Fiberglass windows with frames made from high quality Fiberglass that offer energy efficiency and beauty improving the street appeal of your home by manufacturing them with Fiberglass. Our Fiberglass windows and doors provide durable, reliable, thermally efficient, and cost-effective solutions for your home.

Highest Quality Energy Efficient, Fiberglass Windows with Triple Glazed Glass

We provide the most durable, reliable and thermal efficient triple glazed windows in North America. Our window framing system is Pultruded Fiberglass, meaning we preserve the overall performance of our windows. It does this by providing superior insulation in extreme environments (heat, cold or highly corrosive), high condensation resistance, superior strength to weight ratios and high glass to frame ratios all within a strong, durable, energy efficient Fiberglass frame.

Fibertec is the only company within the Window and Door industry to manufacture a solid fiberglass entrance door frame & slab.

From fabrication to finish to shipping, we develop highly durable fiberglass windows and door frames to ensure we preserve strength and long-term performance. Whatever the weather, whatever the pressure, Fibertec offers a complete range of benefits that meet or exceed Energy Star and LEED criteria and offer the strongest support and best insulation.

CelluRods®, a sustainable functional ingredient

Derived from PEFC certified trees, CelluRods® are high quality sulfated cellulose nanocrystals produced by CelluForce. They are biodegradable and have a very low carbon footprint. They are typically used in small amounts to improve product performance.

CelluRods® come in different grades to match your application requirements.  CelluRods® are available in powder or liquid form.

More Info
Get a Sample
Nanocrystalline cellulose applications for different markets

Nanocrystalline cellulose (NCC) can be used as an advanced biomaterial to enhance performance in a wide array of products in different markets. As sustainability concerns continue to rise, the adoption of CelluRods® cellulose nanocrystals could provide an eco-friendly alternative to traditional materials, unlocking novel solutions for a greener future.

Paints and Coatings

Improve your paints and coatings formulations with CelluRods®. See how they can be used as natural surfactants for 100% biobased paints or to improve scratch resistance, hardness, and toughness.

More info
Packaging

Improve the performance, recyclability and environmental footprint of your packaging constructs. Use CelluRods® to achieve high oxygen barrier or to improve the strength of your package.

More info
Cosmetics

Use our excipient grade CelluRods® to formulate smooth and sustainable cosmetic products. See how they can be used to replace plastic microbeads or to improve the stability and texture of cosmetic formulations.

TIRE AND WHEEL PROTECTION
WE ARE SPECIALISTS IN
Tyre Protector (North America) Inc. offers a clear solution to the challenge of better performance for your vehicle. Our products receive frequent recognition and accreditation from around the world.
TIRE PROTECTOR
THE WORLD`S MOST ADVANCED PUNCTURE PROTECTION SYSTEM
PROTECTS ALL TIRES

TIRE PROTECTOR  is a liquid (gel) puncture sealant that is injected into tubeless, pneumatic tires that offers permanent guaranteed puncture protection for the life of the tire. When a tire that has been treated with Tire Protector encounters a puncture, air pressure inside the tire forces Tire Protector into the wound forming an instant and permanent.

READ MORE
ECOFINS™ HELPS TO REDUCE DRAG EFFECT BY SPINNING THE AIR AS IT LEAVES THE REAR OF THE VEHICLE

 Each vortex lasts several meters in length, keeping the airflow controlled and restricting it from becoming turbulent. This allows the vehicle to move forward more easily as it encounters less drag. The result is a reduction in required energy (fuel) to maintain the required speed. Each EcoFin produces two counter rotating solid body vortices that rotate at approximately 3000 rpm. These vortices are about 4 to 5 inches in diameter and trail behind several meters. They help to reduce turbulence and suction drag at the tractor-trailer gap and at the rear of the trailer.

READ MORE
CENTRABALANCE TECHNOLOGY - STOP WASTING YOUR MONEY!
ACTIVE WHEEL BALANCING SYSTEM is the ONLY solution for the challenges of tire life and performance.

CENTRABALANCE is a self adjusting wheel balancing which offers you guaranteed performance and savings. It works by centrifugal force which precisely positions the liquid in counterweight positions. This will eliminate the problem of tire cupping, reduces vibration resonance making for a smoother ride. Centrabalance also works with gravity to create a down force effect that holds the tire down on the road. This gives the tire more footprint and better control in cold, icy and wet conditions.

READ MORE
ZAMLOK PREVENTS LUG NUT LOSS, WHEEL DAMAGE AND POTENTIAL WHEEL LOSS BY SECURING THE LUG NUTS TOGETHER

Wheel lug nuts can loosen as a result of temperature change as well as wheel vibration.
ZAMLOK is an innovative, new product that uses the resistance between 2 nuts to minimize their ability to rotate and loosen. Any rotation is clearly seen with an indication.
ZAMLOK
Provides a clear visual check of all lug nuts
Reduces the need to replace lug nuts
Reduces risk of wheel damage
Reduces risk of wheel loss and potential liability for personal injury
Reduces risk of loss of life and or property damage

READ MORE
FROZEN BRAKE CHECK - EFFECTIVE & INEXPENSIVE DEVICE
Easy to see if the wheels are turning. Avoids dragging your trailer with frozen brakes.

FROZEN BRAKE CHECK NOTIFYING DRIVERS TO:

– frozen brakes
– frozen air lines
– seized brakes
– easily visible

About Sirius Machine

As an ISO 9001:2015, AS9100D, and IATF 16949 certified precision CNC, wire & tube forming and cold heading machine shop, Sirius Machine specializes in manufacturing low, medium, and high volume quality machined components. We're a privately owned Canadian corporation in Concord, Ontario.

We set out to accomplish this goal by offering the following to our clientele: An onsite manufacturing facility, where custom precision components can be made to order. Bringing Plastic to Shape
Air Molded Plastics, is a recognized leader in plastic blow molding part production.  Some of these products include containers, automotive parts, cases, toys, and household items.  


	
One Step Solution for Complex Parts
The key advantage of Air Molded Plastics is our versatility in both process and product.  Blow molding of complex or critical parts is what we do best.  Depending on the application, the blow molding process allows the integration of several components into one molded part.  Air Molded Plastics’ design staff will engineer your product to maximize this process’s advantage.  We can process various types of new and recycled plastic like high density polyethylene, polypropylene, k-resin, and nylon-6 to meet your product’s demands.  Our “quick mold change” enables us to accommodate varying run requirements.  
Services Offered
Below is a listing of some of the services that Air Molded Plastics offers its customers.  For more information, please contact Air Molded Plastics directly and a representative would be happy to give you a full listing of our services.
Concept-to-Product Project
R&D Support
Air Molded Plastics works with original concepts through preproduction, through to full production. Other parts of this service include concept work, production tooling, design work and prototype tooling.
LEARN MORE
	
Multiple Product Sizes
Air Molded Plastics offers different sizing options for each project; big, small, or in between, Air Molded Plastics can mold each product to exact specifications.
SEE PAST PRODUCTS
	
Customer Service Support
Due to Air Molded Plastics' size, each product receives great attention to detail and care.  We also provide quality customer service for any questions or concerns you may have.

WHAT STARTED AS JUST AN IDEA 40 YEARS AGO, HAS GROWN INTO A HIGHLY SUCCESSFUL COMPANY THAT ELEVATES THE PLASTICS INDUSTRY TO A NEW LEVEL.

MM® Plastic (Mfg.) Co. Inc. is a privately held manufacturing company that began operation in 1962. Our head office is located in Mississauga, Ontario and is comprised of both a manufacturing and warehouse facility. We have an additional manufacturing plant in the Buffalo, NY area.

We are injection molders of high-volume, lightweight plastic products. Our areas of expertise range from the electrical industry to the automotive, consumer products, packaging, fittings and closures businesses. We have the ability to mold a variety of materials, including, but not limited to, nylon, polyethylene, polypropylene, styrene, thermoplastic rubbers, glass-filled nylon, polycarbonate and PVC. MM® Employees work together to creatively satisfy the needs of our broad and diversified customer base.

We hold a number of patents, produce over 700 different products and export throughout North America and Mexico, as well as parts of Asia and the Caribbean.

Our staff is closely involved with UL and CSA on the various harmonization committees in an attempt to not only develop, but to set high industry standards. MM® Plastics believe that by bringing these standards to their highest levels, the result will be a greater safety for the public and end-users.

North America's Injection Molding Specialist.

At Plascon Plastics, we specialize in developing products through injection molding. Located in Vancouver, we provide services to businesses looking for sustainable manufacturing solutions in the North America.

As leaders in plastic manufacturing, we work closely with our clients to find innovative and cost-effective ways to differentiate their injection molded products. Whether that is through the use of PCR and other sustainable materials, or by designing better performing molds, we work with you every step of the way to create products we can all be proud of.

Learn more about our company →

Contact us for a consultation
Our Sustainable Difference.

Plastic products are a global issue. While plastic provides us with many benefits, we must be good stewards in order to make sure that the benefits outweigh the harm. Recycling plastic is not always easy. That is why we pride ourselves as sustainability leaders in the injection molding industry. Our technology allows us to turn waste stream materials into brand new products. Instead of adding to this global problem, we aim to solve it.

Learn more about our services →

Post consumer recycled (PCR) plastics consist of household blue box recyclables. This material is harder to process than post industrial recycled (PIR) plastic.
Many carpet fibres are made out of plastics. Using our technology, these fibres can be separated at the end of their life and made into brand new products.
Our technology allows us to harvest ocean plastics and turn them into brand new products.
Our most recent initiative is to create bio-plastics. This includes plastics that breakdown faster as well as fully bio-degradable materials such as hemp.
Contact us for a consultation
Plascon is a dedicated expert in mold design, product manufacturing, and injection molding.

Our primary emphasis lies in seamlessly integrating eco-friendly materials to assist brands in realizing their sustainability objectives.

With decades of experience in the plastics industry, we identify and capture global opportunities. Our formulas, logistical solutions, and patents have been used across multiple global industries. We also partner with exciting companies and handle all of their operational needs. This includes developing, manufacturing and distribution. We go one step further and have even developed new businesses with previous clients.

Learn more about our clients →

Formed Plastics Without Limits

Creative Form Plastics is a full-service, one-stop thermoforming and fabricating house committed to quality, timely delivery and cost-effective production. Established in 1988, we are a respected supplier within the display, packaging and OEM industries.

View Services
About Us

As part of our commitment to customer service, we have manufacturing facilities in Toronto and Montreal. This allows us to respond quickly to all requests.

Our unique mix of equipment allows us to offer in-house design and tooling, thermoforming, CNC production and fabrication to create custom designed solutions.

Our success is built on trust and we strive to develop long term relationships with our customers and suppliers.

CFP Thinks Green

Creative Form Plastics embraces its social responsibility to be a leader in implementing environmentally sound practices that emphasize sustainability of resources and a reduction of carbon footprint.

The intelligent use of resources and efficient manufacturing can reduce environmental impacts while potentially reducing costs.

Creative Form Plastic has invested significant resources to introduce recyclable materials that meet these goals.

We are using materials that include a recycle content before production.
We capture waste and off-cuts from production and return them to the recycling stream.
We seek out materials that are acceptable to post-retail and post-consumer recycling programs.

For example, we are eliminating PVC and reducing HIPS in production where possible. We have added clear, white and black RPET to our normal inventory. Clear RPET is an excellent alternative for packaging trays. White and black RPET have proven popular for cosmetic, CPG and pharmaceutical displays.

One-Stop Service: BEND. PROTECT. SHIP.

Degree is the only company than can bend your pipe, protect it with our exclusive injection insulation technique, and ship it to your site ready for installation. Unlike insulating pipes with mitred sections of straight insulation, our injected insulation leaves no seams or gaps.

By having your pipes bent and insulated in our shop—instead of insulating bends on-site-you:

Can install your pipeline faster
Reduce the cost of installing your pipeline
Provide your pipes with the maximum protection possible
Extend the service life of your pipes and pipe bends

Whether we bend your pipes, insulate them or both, our dedicated hauling and hot shot service is available to deliver your pipes when and where you need them, so your project isn’t delayed and you can finish on-time and on-budget.

For structural and architectural bending, Degree provides a full range of steel bending capabilities required to transform a blueprint or design into a physical reality.

Disclaimer: The company bios you’re about to read are purely satirical and were crafted by our IT person, who clearly had to much free time. We assure you that our team is both hard-working and dedicated (even if they have quirky hobbies outside of work). Please enjoy with a sense of humor!

IAN FANCY

SALES

Introducing Ian, our sales veteran who’s been here so long, we’re starting to wonder if he came with the building. He’s the voice behind our company’s radio ad—because who better to sell our services than a guy who’s been around long enough to remember when vinyl records were cutting-edge? Between pitching sales and dropping obscure musical references, Ian is the soundtrack of our office.

Ian@novadoorsandwindows.com

MIKE LUXTON

SALES

Meet Mike, our sales guy who’s as passionate about his harmonica playing as he is about his motorcycles. When he’s not revving up his bike, he’s serenading us with his unique harmonica solos—because nothing says 'sales expert' like a solo performance that might make you question your life choices. If you need to hear some 'heartfelt' harmonica riffs or get the lowdown on the latest bike trends, Mike’s your man!

 Mike@novadoorsandwindows.com

KATHELEEN DALLEY

SALES

Kathleen, our sales expert who—if being the mother of Chris wasn’t impressive enough—also has a discerning taste for wine. When she’s not performing miracles in the sales department, she’s indulging in a fine glass of wine, because even saints need their downtime. Kathleen’s knack for balancing divine duties with a taste for the finer things in life is truly remarkable. Kathleen doesn’t have any quirky hobbies that I know of, so it was hard to make fun of her in this bio.

Katheleen@novadoorsandwindows.com

CALE SHANNON

SALES

Introducing Cale, our inside sales guru. When he’s not closing deals, he’s flexing his knowledge of artisanal hops and pondering the next move in his latest chess match—yes, he’ll let you know he plays. Recently, he’s developed an intense, almost Instagram-worthy obsession with the gym. We suspect it’s not about the gains, but rather the glances from ladies at the protein shake counter. Ask him about his workout routine if you have a spare hour… or don’t if you value your time.

Cale@novadoorsandwindows.com

CHRIS DALLEY

SALES

Meet Chris, our outside sales aficionado who spends more time perfecting his espresso shots than actually drinking them. Nothing says 'sales success' like a barista-level brew. On the weekends, he’s probably deep into some mind-numbing strategy game, where excitement peaks at organizing virtual armies. But don’t let his hobbies fool you—Chris is always ready to close a deal… right after he adjusts the grind setting on his coffee grinder.

Chris@novadoorsandwindows.com

GREG BURROWS

SALES

Introducing Greg, our sales rep who somehow balances his love for sports, his Cape Breton pride, and the endless defeats he faces in video games—usually at the hands of his young boys. Whether he’s passionately discussing the latest sports stats or reminiscing about the good ol’ days on the island, Greg is always ready for a challenge… unless it’s a game controller in his hands. Despite his best efforts, his kids regularly hand him a humbling loss. But don’t worry—Greg’s competitive spirit shines in sales, even if he’s benched in the virtual world.

Greg@novadoorsandwindows.com

CREG HAYES

SALES

Say hello to Creg, our outside sales rep who’s always on the go—literally, now that he’s the proud owner of a Volkswagen camper that may or may not start on the first try. A connoisseur of gluten-free beer, Creg enjoys sipping his brew while dreaming of his next road trip. At lunchtime, you’ll find him pulling out a full, home-cooked feast, leaving the rest of us with our sad sandwiches. Whether he’s cruising in his vintage camper or pitching a sale, Creg does it all in style—preferably gluten-free.

Creg@novadoorsandwindows.com

RICHARD HARTENHOF

About Us
	
Our Solid Foundation

Tangibles was founded on innovation, creativity and sensitivity to fulfill our customer’s goals and expectations in every way we have available to us. The same qualities that got us here must and will continue through training and care, Inspiring and guiding every member of our team to produce for our customers nothing less than the very best on time.

Tangibles Founder,
John Ostrovsky

Custom

Custom extrusion and moulding often requires custom finishing and other secondary operations. Additional operations include: Special Cutting, Drilling, Notching, Mitering, Slotting, Routing, Heat Sealing, Sonic Welding, Special Assembly, Labeling, Pad Printing, Hot Stamping, Coiling, Custom Boxing, Shrink Wrapping and multiple Face Taping. Being a 100% custom shop, we provide our customers with a finished custom part.

Technology

On the cutting edge of custom thermoplastic moulding and plastic profile extrusion since 1979, Tangibles Ltd. has achieved an exceptional level of quality and service in the plastic injection moulding and plastic profile extrusion industry. At Tangibles Ltd., quality begins with our expert precision in-house tool and die department. These experienced craftsmen produce high quality tooling to ensure that your plastic parts are manufactured to your precise requirements.

Facility

Our large 50,000 square foot facility located in Toronto enables us to have the unique ability to meet your injection moulding and extrusion needs under one roof. With our 2½” and 3½” extrusion lines, we have the capability to manufacture extrusions for any application. We have co-extrusion capabilities for dual and triple extrusions as well as multiple extruded color combinations. Our numerous on-line cutters and punches allows Tangibles to offer customers a variety of cutting tolerances, slitting or punching capabilities. Our array of injection moulding machinery starts as small as 90 tonnes and up to 350 tonnes.

Challenge Us

We invite our customers to challenge us with their special extrusion needs and difficult manufacturing problems. Our experience provides us with the capability to develop solutions. Developing partnerships with our customer is important in our commitment to provide total customer satisfaction.

 

Selection

The options available to Tangibles customers extend to material selection as well. Commodity and engineered compounds are available to meet specific design requirements. These include: LDPE, MDPE, HDPE, ABS, PVC (Flexible & Rigid), Polypropylene, Polystyrene, HIPS, Butyrate, SAN, Nylon, PETG, Polycarbonate, Acrylic, TPR, Crystal Styrene, Polyurethane, and many others… All materials are available as transparent or opaque, with colour matching available.

Unique

Our business is different than a typical commodity shop. We have an acute awareness of the complexities of designing plastics. Quality parts, blanket order programs, part warehousing and Just in Time capabilities are only part of the total picture. Our quality assurance programs are in place to ensure our customer’s satisfaction. All our products are designed with state-of-the-art CAD software, coupled with our in-house wire EDM machine capabilities, enable us to produce extremely complex and precise moulded parts and extrusion profiles.

Welcome to Blaze Plastics!

As a leading manufacturer and supplier of plastic tanks in Alberta, we offer a full range of high quality tanks in a variety of sizes to meet any need you might have. Need rotationally molded high-capacity containment basins for your oilfield? Not a problem. What about septic tanks for office or residential purposes? We’ve got that covered as well… and everything in between!

Using only the highest quality corrosion resistant polyethylene resin, and incorporating the latest advancements in plastic welding and seamless rotational molding, we are your go-to source for any poly tank needs you might have. Some of our products include:

Water tanks, from basic models to industrial storage solutions. Our plastic water tanks keep your supply fresh and clean.
Septic tanks in a host of shapes and sizes. Whatever your sewage management needs, we offer the strongest and most reliable solutions.
Storage tanks and containment basins for the storing of materials at any scale.
RV tanks for those who want a reliable way to keep their water contained and contaminant-free while leading a fast-paced on the go lifestyle.

Note that we also do quite a bit of custom work! Need an odd size? How about rectangular tanks? If our standard models aren’t what you’re looking for, we can gladly create something that meets your needs. We have a long history of providing custom proprietary plastic tanks to the oil, gas, and agricultural industries.

Blaze Plastics takes pride in being locally owned and operated here just outside Camrose, Alberta, Canada. That said, we also take seriously our obligation to provide quality service to as many people as possible. We feel that, when it comes to water tanks, Canada is a ripe market and we’re more than happy to arrange delivery service to a variety of Alberta locations including Leduc, Nisku, Red Deer, and Calgary.

In regards to plastic water tanks, Edmonton is one of our biggest service areas. Additionally, locations as diverse as Fort McMurray and Grande Prairie make frequent use of our products in oil sands projects. We’re all over the place, and we leave a reputation for quality everywhere we go, so you can put your trust in us no matter where you operate.

Feel free to take a look around our site to get a sense of what kinds of high quality products we offer, and what we can do to serve you. If you have any questions whatsoever, don’t hesitate to contact us. We’re here to serve you!

Maljohn manufactures custom plastic components for use on equipment and surfaces that undergo constant impact and abrasion.

Our products are designed for use in agriculture, mining, food processing, and many more industrial and materials handling applications.

VIEW PRODUCT CATALOGUE
About Maljohn

Maljohn Company was conceived and commenced in the spring of 1976. Originally as a ‘Rep’ company searching out products to provide abrasion resistance products to the Canadian and U.S. grain handling industry. At that time little or no plastics products were used in either small or large grain elevators.

Our first products manufactured in Hamilton in 1978 included flex loading spouts (originally used in prairie grain elevators for box car loading); flat and round bottom drag conveyor flights and paddles; rollers and roller assemblies, all custom made to order.

WELCOME TO METELIX PRODUCTS INC.

Metelix Products Inc. is a leading-edge custom plastics blow molding manufacturer. We specialize in the total integration of building plastic products from concept, through design and tooling to the finished product. We also provide assembling of the final product with component parts if necessary and shipping of the order anywhere in the world. Our business partners like our “one stop shop” approach.

​

A significant part of our business is in plastic automotive parts with the required certificates necessary to maintain the quality and delivery standards required in the auto industry. This achievement of quality manufacturing also applies to our commercial and industrial products. 

 

Precision metal machining / fabrication is another avenue for business at Metelix Products Inc. The tool and die makers and metal machine experts in the Metelix tool shop can handle intricate metal jobs.

 

Our unique ability to move from concept to finished product is an overall feature that benefits our customers, yielding much of our success. Metelix is also known to update older products, improve performance and/or aesthetics of existing products as well as designing and engineering new ones.

​

We look forward to discussing your ideas and products, so please contact our customer service team with any inquiries.

We are now a part of the Inteplast Group, one of the largest manufacturers of Can Liners in North America.

Established in the 1950’s, W. Ralston has become Canada’s market leader in waste management solutions. Our dedication to Quality, Service, Consistency and Innovation has been our top priority since the beginning.

Our steady growth has allowed us to expand across Canada into two manufacturing facilities in Brampton Ontario and Drumheller Alberta. Along with three warehouse facilities, we continue to expand in order to support our growing North American customer base.

Custom Thermoformed Plastic Packaging

Elmes Packaging specializes in custom thin gauge thermoforming. Our designs are made to your exact specifications using the highest quality materials.

LEARN MORE
Our Commitment

We pride ourselves on providing superior service and high-quality products to our customers. Since our founding in 1975, we have been committed to delivering exceptional packaging solutions from our facility in Mississauga, Ontario, serving clients across Canada, the U.S., and Europe.

Products
Previous

Thermoformed plastic trays and lids have a wide variety of uses, including retail packaging and shipping trays.

Formed plastic trays make for effective inserts to keep products in place inside cartons or other boxes.

ESD (Electrostatic Dissipative) packaging that protects products from static damage as well as impact and vibration during shipping.

Clamshells are a one-piece product that can be securely closed by built-in locks or ultrasonic welding/shrink film.

Blister packaging involves using a custom formed plastic blister that is then usually sealed onto a printed back made of card-stock.

Technology and Innovation

Our strength combines innovative design with state-of-the-art technology to create solutions to the most demanding thermoformed packaging challenges. Whether you require intricate, multi-cavity, nesting/stackable trays and clamshells or simple, single-cavity shipping platforms, we work with you through all phases of the product development cycle to design packaging to your exact specifications.

LEARN MORE
Thermoforming Experts

We are your thin-gauge thermoforming experts. The process involves heating a thin sheet of plastic until it becomes pliable, then shaping it over a mold to create precise, durable, and lightweight packaging solutions. The finished product is ideal for a wide range of packaging applications suitable for nearly every industry.

LEARN MORE
Customer Experience

Partnerships are at the center of everything we do. Our products are developed using the highest quality plastics and service is a priority. We respond to all inquiries by the next business day and the efficiency of our process allows us to deliver cost-effective packaging solutions significantly faster than our competitors.

We have polluted our world, poisoned our waterways, damaged the air we breathe, and destroyed the soil we depend on for food. 

Plastic pollution is a reminder to all of us that plastic has served us well for the last 70 years but if we are to survive and prosper we need to find sustainable solutions and products.

In our state-of-the-art laboratory, we keep investing in new methods of enhancing our existing products, without compromising our beliefs.

We believe in acting with integrity in everything we do, irrespective of personal sacrifice or cost. We believe that the client is our most valuable asset and their trust in our products and services cannot be betrayed. 

We strive to be the best in everything we do. We target excellence as an objective. 

We believe that profitable operations are important but taking care of Mother Earth, not polluting our environment are more important. We believe in leaving a better, cleaner world to the future generations.

Specialty Packaging

Specialty packaging can include film products, single life use products, trays, FDA approved products, foam or air filled products, courier and bank security bags, envelope windows and ziplock products.

Retail
Retail uses are among the largest categories of single use life products. If it’s plastic and you need it, we can make it.
Bottles/Containers/
Closures/Utensils/Straws
Bottles, Containers, Closures, Utensils and Straws consume billions of pounds of plastic every year, let’s make them biodegradable!
Agriculture
Agricultural uses are very important to our continued success in harvesting enough food globally for the population of the world. Our mulch film is offered in biodegradable, compostable, photo-degradable, conventional and barrier film.
Waste
Waste use plastics are among the heaviest used plastics in the world and in many cases can provide the largest problems for the world. Let’s make the earth healthier together by using our 100% recycled and biodegradable waste products.

There’s Never Been a Better Time to Choose PolyJohn

PolyJohn has been a mainstay in the portable sanitation industry for decades and a major driving force in its growth through our innovative products, membership and support of the PSAI and other activities. Our company takes pride in manufacturing the most durable products on the market and backing them 100%. We also employ a team of industry experts who put our customers first and go above and beyond to help them in any way possible.

We aren't a company that rests on our laurels and is satisfied with our past successes. Our team is constantly looking for ways to better serve our customers. THE POLYJOHN LEGACY: SERVING PROS FOR THREE GENERATIONS

PolyJohn is a family-owned and -operated business that has been helping portable restroom operators (PROs) grow their businesses since 1984. Co-founded by Ed Cooper, PolyJohn expanded and thrived thanks to the driving force of knowing, “when our customers are successful, we are successful.” Ed’s sons Mike and Ken assumed ownership of the company after his passing in 2017 and have taken the company to new heights. Today, PolyJohn continues to fulfill Ed’s dream and is poised to remain an industry leader with the third generation — Sam and Gus — continuing the legacy.

What has and will continue to set PolyJohn apart are:

High-Quality Portable Sanitation Products
Experienced, Helpful Employees
Lasting Relationships — You’re Not Just a Customer, You're a Friend
More Than Products — JohnTalk Content & Portable Restroom Business Marketing Support

To learn more about PolyJohn's legacy, watch our video.

POLYJOHN: WORLD-CLASS MANUFACTURING HEADQUARTERED IN THE USA
PolyJohn is a worldwide manufacturer of portable toilets, portable sinks and accessories based in Whiting, Indiana. Manufacturing in-house allows us to control every aspect of the manufacturing process — from raw materials to final product — and set the standard for high quality and innovation. When you purchase from PolyJohn, you get products backed by:
Best-in-Class Materials
Proven, Dependable Manufacturing Processes
Knowledgeable, Experienced Craftsmen
Meticulous Quality Control
An Enormous Stock of Replacement Parts

Why A 20x25x4 Air Filter Is Essential For Home Air Quality

Indoor air quality is a vital aspect of maintaining a healthy home environment. Air pollution can cause respiratory issues, allergies and aggravate existing medical conditions like asthma. As such, it is essential to take measures to ensure that the air inside your house is clean and safe for breathing. One way to achieve this is by installing an effective air filtration system in your HVAC unit. This article aims to explore why using a high-quality 20x25x4 filter is crucial for ensuring good indoor air quality and how it can benefit homeowners in terms of health and cost savings over time.

Understanding The Importance Of Air Filters For Home Health

As human beings, we spend the majority of our time indoors. Thus, it is essential to maintain a healthy indoor environment to promote overall well-being. One way to achieve this is by ensuring that air filters in our homes are efficient and regularly maintained. Air filters in the HVAC unit are responsible for removing dust, pollen, and other airborne particles from the air. This helps to keep the air inside your home clean and safe for breathing.

Installing a high-quality 20x25x4 filter is essential for ensuring maximum filtration of airborne pollutants. These filters are designed with dense pleats, constructed out of a combination of synthetic and natural fibers. This allows them to capture even the smallest particles, while still allowing adequate airflow in your HVAC system.

The Benefits Of A 20x25x4 Air Filter

Having established the importance of air filters in maintaining a healthy home environment, it is crucial to consider the benefits of using a 20x25x4 air filter.

Improved Air Quality: A 20x25x4 air filter has a larger surface area and thickness, which makes it capable of capturing more dust, pollen, and other airborne contaminants. This can greatly improve the overall air quality in the home, reducing allergy symptoms and promoting better respiratory health.
Cost Savings: While a 20x25x4 air filter may be more expensive upfront, it can actually save money in the long run. Because it captures more contaminants, it can extend the lifespan of HVAC systems and reduce the need for costly repairs or replacements.
Energy Efficiency: A clean air filter allows air to flow more freely through the HVAC system, which can improve energy efficiency and lower utility bills.
Convenience: A 20x25x4 air filter typically needs to be changed less frequently than standard air filters, which can save time and hassle for homeowners.
Increased Comfort: Improved air quality and energy efficiency can also contribute to a more comfortable home environment, with consistent temperatures and reduced humidity levels.

It's clear that a 20x25x4 air filter is essential for improving indoor quality, promoting home health, and ultimately reducing costs over time. For these reasons, homeowners should opt for this type of high-quality filter when looking to enhance the air filtration system in their HVAC units.

How A 20x25x4 Air Filter Captures Harmful Particles

Filter efficiency is a critical factor in determining the effectiveness of air filters. A 20x25x4 air filter has an excellent filtering capacity due to its high-efficiency rate. The filter captures harmful particles such as pollen, dust mites, and pet dander with ease because of its dense filtration material. The pleated design increases the surface area available for capturing contaminants, ensuring that more pollutants are trapped within the filter.

Particle retention is another essential aspect of an effective air filter. This specification refers to how well the filter can retain particles after it traps them. A 20x25x4 air filter's advanced air filtration technology ensures that once pollutants are captured, they remain within the filter until it is time for a replacement. Therefore, homeowners do not have to worry about allergens or pollutants being released back into their homes' atmosphere, thereby improving indoor air quality significantly.

Improving Indoor Air Quality With A 20x25x4 Air Filter

As discussed in the previous section, a 20x25x4 air filter effectively captures harmful particles that can negatively impact indoor air quality. However, it is not enough to have just any air filter installed in your home. Air filter efficiency plays an essential role in improving indoor air quality since it determines how well the unit collects and traps pollutants.

In addition to efficiency, replacement frequency, and cost-effectiveness are critical factors when choosing the right air filter for your home. Frequent replacements ensure that the unit continues to work at optimal levels without clogging or becoming less efficient over time. While some high-efficiency filters may come with a higher price tag, they save money in the long run by reducing energy costs associated with heating and cooling systems while also providing clean air for occupants' health benefits. Therefore, installing a 20x25x4 air filter is crucial for maintaining healthy indoor air quality as it provides excellent filtration capabilities while being cost-effective and easy to replace regularly.

Where To Purchase An 20x25x4 Air Filter

If you're looking to purchase a 20x25x4 air filter, there are several options available to you. You can search online by typing "20x25x4 air filter" into your favorite search engine. You'll typically find a range of products from reputable online retailers to choose from. Additionally, you can check with local hardware or home improvement stores to see if they carry this size of the filter.

It's important to make sure you choose the correct filter size and type for your HVAC system to ensure maximum efficiency and air quality. Don't forget to check for discounts and promotions that may be available to save you some money.

Factors To Consider When Choosing An Air Filter Size

When choosing an air filter size, there are several factors to consider. One of the most important is filter efficiency.

Airflow: The size of the air filter should allow for adequate airflow to ensure proper ventilation and circulation in your space.
MERV rating: The Minimum Efficiency Reporting Value (MERV) rating of the air filter should be considered when choosing the filter size. A higher MERV rating indicates a more efficient filter, but it may also restrict airflow if the filter is too small.
Room size: The size of the room where the air filter will be used should be considered when choosing the filter size. Larger rooms may require larger filters to adequately filter the air.
HVAC system: The size of the air filter should be compatible with your HVAC system. Check the manufacturer's recommendations for the correct size filter for your system.
Type of filter: The type of filter should also be considered when choosing the size. Some filters are designed for specific purposes, such as removing allergens or odors, and may require a specific size.
Budget: The cost of air filters can vary based on size and type. Consider your budget when choosing the size of the filter.

By considering these factors, you can be sure to choose the right size filter for your space and HVAC system and ensure proper ventilation and indoor air quality.

Overall, installing a 20x25x4 air filter is an essential step toward improving indoor air quality in larger homes with central HVAC systems. By dispelling common misconceptions around filter selection and maintenance requirements while highlighting their benefits when used correctly, homeowners can make informed decisions regarding air filtration options.

Contact An Air Filter Supplier

If you are looking for an air filter supplier that can provide you with quality 20x25x4 filters, then look no further than, Filterbuy, Inc. They are a company that provides high-quality air filters for homes and businesses. Their 20x25x4 air filter is one of their best products, designed to provide superior air quality and filtration. This air filter is perfect for those who suffer from allergies and respiratory issues, as it can effectively remove allergens, dust, and other harmful particles from the air. The 20x25x4 air filter is also easy to install and maintain, making it a convenient choice for busy homeowners and business owners. With Filterbuy, Inc., you can trust that you are getting a reliable product that will keep your air clean and healthy. So, if you're looking for a top-of-the-line air filter, look no further than Filterbuy, Inc. and their 20x25x4 air filter.
