Welcome to MSB

Since 1987, MSB Industries have been steadily expanding and has become one of the Toronto areas leading companies of small to medium size Plastics Injection Moulds. With 14,000 square feet of manufacturing and warehouse space, we are a full-service design, build and run facility, specializing in close tolerance parts.  Our services include Part Design, Mould Design, Mould Manufacturing, Production moulding, and final Part Assembly. Our 5 value added services are all performed and controlled in house to ensure our customer receives the best quality products when working with MSB.

Covid19 Mask Accessory - Canadian Made

Canadians stepping up for the fight against COVID-19 – read more…

Our Services
Part Design

Our team of Part Designers can engineer your product from a concept drawing, hand sketch, or simply just an idea.   A wealth of experience and knowledge provides our customers with a “design for moulding” approach, simplifying the mould manufacturing process, reducing production cycle times, and ensuring our customers receive the best value in there part design and tooling.

Production Moulding

The Moulding department produces 5 days per week with a wide variety of 16 moulding machines that range in size from 30 to 200 tons. Our facility’s capabilities range from prototype tooling and material sampling to single/multi-cavity production serving the automotive, food and general consumer markets. We are ISO 9001 certified and continue to build upon our reputation for exceptional quality and attention to detail. Our quality labs strict operating conditions and frequent component inspections strengthen our primary objective of “zero rejects” shipped to our customer.

Mould Design

Our experienced engineers are proud of their established track record of meeting customers’ individualized requirements.  Our commitment to latest CAD software ensures our team has the tools needed to work directly with customer-supplied data. Having total control over this process ensures all our customer requirements are met upfront and streamlines all subsequent processes.

Part Assembly

Often multiple components require hand assembly or automation to complete the final product, this service is of great value to our customers as we can ship the final assembled product to our customer reducing the need for logistics and sourcing of secondary operations, ultimately saving our customer time and money.

Manufacturing

MSB’s commitment to the latest and newest machine technologies provides our customer with quality and accuracy needed for today’s high tolerance fast paced demands.  Our investment in CNC grinding, CNC milling, and CNC EDM technologies ensures all requirements are met at this stage of the product realization process.  Attention to detail, “manufacture to print” practices, and premium steel selection result in your mould perfectly crafted to your specifications.

Pioneers of Custom Orthotics

Footletic Inc. was founded by a group of Canadian Certified Pedorthists with one goal in mind: To provide the most accurate foot orthoses.

E
	
OUR APPROACH

Our approach is to couple traditional foot orthoses manufacturing principles with the latest technologies
available today. We hold multiple CAD orthoses designing software licenses.

E
	
OUR FOCUS

Footletic’s manufacturing process focuses on precision
devices with a complete solution for any orthotic practice.

E
	
ONLINE ORDERING

We offer an online ordering orthotic ordering system. This system is customized to the individual clinician and his/her needs. This proprietary system is built on the back of feedback and our experience of over 45 years in both clinical and manufacturing of foot orthoses.

E
	
CLINICIANS AT HEART

We understand what clinicians require. Our lab consists of Canadian Certified Pedorthists who are members of the Pedorthic Association of Canada as well as the College of Pedorthics of Canada.

Our Products

We ensure that our materials are particularly suited to sports medicine and pediatric applications.

E
	
POLYNYLON

Polynylon- is a proprietary, boradiene, modified high density polyethylene with excellent forming, appearance and impact characteristics. Particularly suited to sports medicine or pediatric applications

Available Thicknesses:

1.5mm Clear

2.0mm Clear

2.5mm Clear

3.0mm Clear

E
	
POLYPROPYLENE

Polypropylene- is a thermoplastic material used to fabricate braces and other supportive devices. The ability of polypropylene to yield pressure and torque, yet consistently return to its original form without fatiguing, has eliminated distortion previously encountered in many orthoses.

Top Covers

For top covers, we use SPENCO® INSOLE MATERIAL, P-CELL® + PORON®,
and perforated MULTIFOAM. These materials may be applied to a variety
of athletic problems, sports devices, diabetic needs, and arthritic problems.

E
	
SPENCO INSOLE MATERIAL

A neoprene sponge, nitrogen induced to absorb lateral or side to side forces as well as vertical pressure. A multi stretch nylon fabric is bonded to one side allowing the foot or extremity to glide easily. Spenco material is decay resistant, odor resistant, and can be cut, skived, and laundered. Ideally suited for patients who have blisters, trophic ulcers, arthritis, diabetes, and for athletes.

E
	
P-CELL® + PORON®

15-20 Durometer + Soft Supporting top cover for applications of sensitive foot conditions such as diabetic and arthritic conditions.

E
	
MULTIFOAM – PERFORATED

A unique material for a number of foot orthotic applications. Especially suitable for difficult foot problems. May be applied to a variety of athletic problems and sports devices.

Technology
E
	
Structure Scanner by Occipital with the Footletic iPad App

Use of the Structure Sensor is reinventing patient care across the fields of orthotics and prosthetics. Applications using Structure Sensor can capture 3D models of any body part for custom-fit prosthetics, orthotics, braces, custom insoles, and much more.

E
	
VeriScan Podriatic Scanner (VPS) Envisic

Utilizing red line-laser 3D-imaging techniques,
the VeriScan Podiatric Scanner quickly
and accurately captures a true-dimension
digital cast of the human foot.

Social Media Marketing for Link Building: Top Tactics & Strategies
 admin November 16, 2018

In the world of SEO, social media marketing isn’t very clear to many people. Most businesses are very agnostic about the use of social media as they think that it can affect their rankings. Although, some prefer to hold SEO and Social Media Marketing as a separate entity; however, Toronto SEO firm Toronto feels that both of them are the same.

Those who hold social media marketing and SEO as separate entity; they simply do it because SEO and social media marketing have got different goals and methods. Often, SEO professionals are making use of social media as a part of their link building strategy.

 

Successful Sites

Major brands or businesses are hopping on the social media bandwagon. It has been observed that social media marketing forms an important part of SEO as it can help in the ranking of the site.

Toronto SEO firm feels that if businesses fail to implement social media marketing within their SEO campaign they can miss out the targeted traffic. Often, SEO experts take the help of social media for link building. This is because link building can help businesses to reach out to target customers.

From a recent survey, it has been observed that:

88% of SEOs include links in social media profile.
53% have experimented with viral campaigns.

Hence, it can be seen that link building with social media is a popular stratagem. If you too are interested to try it out for your business, follow the rest of the blog.

 

Include Links in Social Media Profile

One can’t just simply ignore social media link building just because it’s a nofollow. Social backlinks for SEO is important and for this reason Facebook allows to add website link under the website filed. Toronto SEO firm states that website URL needs to be posted when one posts something on their wall.

 

Invite People to Read Your Content

In order to promote content, care should be taken to make the content engaging and concise. Content can carry link to a homepage. While posting a content one must ensure that it is easily discoverable and related to current topic. As a part of marketing campaign, it is important to look out for niche websites where content can get more exposure

 

Creating Viral Content

One great way to make a social media campaign go viral is by aiming it for teens and adults. Toronto SEO firm experts feel that in order to keep up with the campaign keeping up the conversation with the audience is important. Engaging with audience on real time can help a campaign to go viral and earn loads of links and traffic.

 

Remaining Creative

Creating a content that is popular right at the moment can be a great way to attract traffic. Even when imitating your competitor’s content, your content needs to stand out. Creating stunning messages on social media channels can help in link building.

Toronto SEO firm feels that link building with social media can be very effective for a business. Whether one wants to gain links through social media profile or by creating a viral content, it can help a business in improving their rank.

Terpac - De plus en plus innovant, centré client, socialement responsable


Chers amis,


Terpac est bien plus qu'une simple entreprise de fabrication de cintres. Terpac est une entreprise multinationale innovante, utilisant des partenariats stratégiques dans de nombreux sites de fabrication dans le monde avec des équipes expérimentées pour répondre à tous les besoins en matière de suspension des détaillants et des fabricants de vêtements.

Terpac Plastics International est en activité depuis plus de 30 ans et fournit des cintres de qualité. pour de nombreux programmes de vente au détail et G.O.H. (vêtements sur cintres), petits et grands.

Le marché mondial d'aujourd'hui exige que le fabricant de cintres soit de plus en plus innovant, centré sur le client et socialement responsable. Terpac fabrique des centaines de modèles de cintres pouvant être produits dans différentes couleurs ou matériaux, à la fois en plastique et en bois, et incluant des caractéristiques de haute technologie avec des revêtements antidérapants ou du caoutchouc co-injecté.

Être répertorié dans les programmes officiellement nominés avec Les programmes de marques privées et de réapprovisionnement des magasins de Wal-Mart et de Wal-Mart Canada confirment notre engagement envers la qualité, le prix et la fiabilité. Avec un leadership ciblé et un esprit d'entreprise, Terpac n'est pas trop grand pour perdre de vue notre ressource la plus importante, le client. L'engagement envers le service client, le respect des dates de livraison requises, le suivi immédiat des préoccupations des clients et le souci du détail nous distinguent des autres acteurs de l'industrie.

Terpac possède des installations de production dans le nord et le sud de la Chine (5 installations incluant l'usine de cintres en bois), 3 au Bangladesh, au Mexique, en Inde, au Cambodge et notre usine de fabrication du siège social à Montréal au Canada et notre bureau de vente aux États-Unis.

La qualité est toujours une considération importante chez Terpac; tous nos cintres répondent aux directives strictes énoncées dans les directives VICS/GS1 en matière de qualité, de durabilité et de sécurité. En fait, Terpac est l'une des sociétés responsables de la récente révision des spécifications/directives des cintres pour VICS/GS1. La qualité de tous nos cintres est vérifiée non seulement sur les machines de production, mais un protocole secondaire est effectué au niveau de l'usine et périodiquement, les cintres sont envoyés à des laboratoires d'essais indépendants pour certification. Notre relation avec Wal-Mart exige que toutes les normes éthiques soient respectées en matière de salaires et d'âge ainsi que de procédures environnementales et de sécurité dans toutes nos usines.

Comprenant qu'il existe aujourd'hui de nombreux choix sur le marché des cintres, Terpac souhaite serait honoré si on lui accordait l'opportunité de fournir des cintres pour l'un des besoins de votre entreprise et irait au-delà de vos attentes pour vous rendre fier de votre choix.

INNOVATIVE SAFETY SYSTEMS FOR DIESEL AND SPARK IGNITED ENGINES
Headwind Solutions will keep you safe with advanced gas detection and engine shut off systems for diesel engine runaway and ignition hazards.

Headwind has two featured products that we’ve designed and patented in-house – the ShockerPASS and ShockerEDGE. Our team has worked in the industry for decades to create the highest quality products to keep people safe. Diesel engine runaway can have catastrophic effects leading to loss of property, injuries, work delays, and even death of personnel in the area. We’re committed to advancing safety and share the value of protecting lives, property, businesses, and the environment. We develop solutions that support crisis management plans, and other precautionary measures to increase safety in a workplace.

We want to help keep your worksite safe and productive through the use of advanced detection and engine shut off technology! Have some questions about how our innovative safety systems can help your business?

Contact Us Today
INTRODUCING
ShockerEDGE

This innovative technology is the first of its kind and works for all internal combustion engines. We install a state-of-the-art MPS gas sensor in the air intake system of the engine that reads flammable gases. It calibrates itself every two seconds using ambient temperature, barometric pressure, and relative humidity. ShockerEDGE can turn your engine off before a diesel runaway or ignition sources from hot surfaces become an issue. Other uses for ShockerEDGE include.  diesel engine emergency shutdown, early detection and notification on engines for first responders, production and service personal.

Learn More
MAIN SCREEN EVENTS
The data is also sent to the display, giving you a real time display of the sensors findings including;
System and sensor status
Temperature, humidity, and barometric pressure
Settings tab
Gas status and identification
Concentration of gas detected
Alarm Status
Data logging
Why You Need the ShockerEDGE
STATE-OF-THE-ART TECHNOLOGY
State-of-the-art MPS gas sensor in the air intake system of the engine, that reads flammable gasses. Unlike Cat bead/Pellister type sensors, the MPS gas sensor calibrates itself every 2 seconds using up to date ambient temperature, barometric pressure, and relative humidity. It does not require bump gas, docking stations or an instrument technician to recalibrate 4 times a year.
SECURE DATA TRANSMISSION
The sensor reads the chemical composition of the air being drawn into the engine, then transmits the data to the ShockerEDGE controller and the ShockerEDGE display.
FASTER & SAFER THEN EVER
Once the data is received by the controller, it can be programmed to turn the engine off at 7.5% LEL, long before a diesel engine runaway can occur, or a gasoline engine starts to backfire. The controller can also be programmed to activate your ShockerPASS air shutoff valve on a diesel engine.
Also from Headwind Solutions
Preventing Diesel Engine Runaway

Positive air intake shut off systems prevent diesel engine runaway. A diesel engine will utilize any fuel available, and flammable gas in the air is more than enough to keep a diesel engine running, even when the key is removed. Once a diesel engine gets a supply of flammable gas in the air, it will run indefinitely to the point of catastrophic failure. The only way to prevent and stop this is to starve it of gaseous fuel. By installing the ShockerPASS, or ShockerEDGE you cut off the flammable gas before a diesel runaway can occur.

Contact Us Today
ShockerPASS

We manufacture the best available automatic positive air shutoff systems to prevent diesel runaways. Our original product, the ShockerPASS is a positive air-shutoff system that automatically senses high-revving runaway situation and shuts the valve to the diesel engine. By closing the air supply, we protect personnel in the area, your property, and the engine itself. Don’t worry about diesel runaway with this high quality shut off system!

Learn More

Just received our full North American patent for our products great way to start 2021.

Why you need the SHOCKERPASS
SECURITY AND SAFETY
A positive air shutoff system is a necessity for anyone with a diesel engine that may come in contact with natural gas, propane, or any other flammable gasses. A small leak of flammable gas is likely to cause a diesel engine to “run away”, causing catastrophic damage to the engine, and surrounding area as it explodes.
PREVENTS CATASTROPHIC FAILURE
A diesel engine will utilize any fuel available, and flammable gas in the air is more than enough to keep a diesel engine running, even when the key is removed. Once a diesel engine gets a supply of flammable gas in the air, it will run indefinitely or to the point of catastrophic failure. The only way to prevent and stop this is to shut off the air supply to the engine, starving it of gaseous fuel.
SMART SENSORS
The Shocker Positive Air Shutoff System is capable of automatically sensing high-revving “run away” situations, and will automatically shut the valve, closing the air supply to the engine to protect the engine itself, as well as property and personnel in the area.

We have pre-built kits for most positive air shutoff systems. If you have equipment we have not yet developed a kit for, our dedicated R&D department will custom build a kit for your specific application.

Aluminum Stamping Solutions

One of the most frequent problems encountered with perforating aluminum is punch galling. Aluminum, in general, possesses a gummy characteristic which causes it to adhere to a surface of the punch when it's drawn, pulled, trimmed, perforated, or pierced. This accumulation of material on the punch is known as galling (adhesive wear). The galling occurs both on the initial penetration into the material and extraction from the material.
